186  llvm::is_integral_or_enum<T>::value;

206 static auto makeBooleanOptionNormalizer(bool Value, bool OtherValue,
207  OptSpecifier OtherOpt) {
208  return [Value, OtherValue, OtherOpt](OptSpecifier Opt, unsigned,
209  const ArgList &Args,
210  DiagnosticsEngine &) -> Optional<bool> {
211  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(Opt, OtherOpt)) {
212  return A->getOption().matches(Opt) ? Value : OtherValue;
213  }
214  return None;
215  };

227 static void denormalizeStringImpl(SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
228  const char *Spelling,
229  CompilerInvocation::StringAllocator SA,
230  Option::OptionClass OptClass, unsigned,
231  const Twine &Value) {
232  switch (OptClass) {
233  case Option::SeparateClass:
234  case Option::JoinedOrSeparateClass:
235  case Option::JoinedAndSeparateClass:
236  Args.push_back(Spelling);
237  Args.push_back(SA(Value));
238  break;
239  case Option::JoinedClass:
240  case Option::CommaJoinedClass:
241  Args.push_back(SA(Twine(Spelling) + Value));
242  break;
243  default:
244  llvm_unreachable("Cannot denormalize an option with option class "
245  "incompatible with string denormalization.");
246  }
247 }

249 template <typename T>
250 static void
251 denormalizeString(SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args, const char *Spelling,
252  CompilerInvocation::StringAllocator SA,
253  Option::OptionClass OptClass, unsigned TableIndex, T Value) {
254  denormalizeStringImpl(Args, Spelling, SA, OptClass, TableIndex, Twine(Value));
255 }

257 static Optional<SimpleEnumValue>
258 findValueTableByName(const SimpleEnumValueTable &Table, StringRef Name) {
259  for (int I = 0, E = Table.Size; I != E; ++I)
260  if (Name == Table.Table[I].Name)
261  return Table.Table[I];
262 
263  return None;
264 }
265 
266 static Optional<SimpleEnumValue>
267 findValueTableByValue(const SimpleEnumValueTable &Table, unsigned Value) {
268  for (int I = 0, E = Table.Size; I != E; ++I)
269  if (Value == Table.Table[I].Value)
270  return Table.Table[I];
271 
272  return None;
273 }

275 static llvm::Optional<unsigned> normalizeSimpleEnum(OptSpecifier Opt,
276  unsigned TableIndex,
277  const ArgList &Args,
278  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
279  assert(TableIndex < SimpleEnumValueTablesSize);
280  const SimpleEnumValueTable &Table = SimpleEnumValueTables[TableIndex];
281 
282  auto *Arg = Args.getLastArg(Opt);
283  if (!Arg)
284  return None;
285 
286  StringRef ArgValue = Arg->getValue();
287  if (auto MaybeEnumVal = findValueTableByName(Table, ArgValue))
288  return MaybeEnumVal->Value;
289 
290  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
291  << Arg->getAsString(Args) << ArgValue;
292  return None;
293 }

295 static void denormalizeSimpleEnumImpl(SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
296  const char *Spelling,
297  CompilerInvocation::StringAllocator SA,
298  Option::OptionClass OptClass,
299  unsigned TableIndex, unsigned Value) {
300  assert(TableIndex < SimpleEnumValueTablesSize);
301  const SimpleEnumValueTable &Table = SimpleEnumValueTables[TableIndex];
302  if (auto MaybeEnumVal = findValueTableByValue(Table, Value)) {
303  denormalizeString(Args, Spelling, SA, OptClass, TableIndex,
304  MaybeEnumVal->Name);
305  } else {
306  llvm_unreachable("The simple enum value was not correctly defined in "
307  "the tablegen option description");
308  }
309 }

330 template <typename IntTy>
331 static Optional<IntTy> normalizeStringIntegral(OptSpecifier Opt, int,
332  const ArgList &Args,
333  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
334  auto *Arg = Args.getLastArg(Opt);
335  if (!Arg)
336  return None;
337  IntTy Res;
338  if (StringRef(Arg->getValue()).getAsInteger(0, Res)) {
339  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_int_value)
340  << Arg->getAsString(Args) << Arg->getValue();
341  return None;
342  }
343  return Res;
344 }

352 static void denormalizeStringVector(SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
353  const char *Spelling,
354  CompilerInvocation::StringAllocator SA,
355  Option::OptionClass OptClass,
356  unsigned TableIndex,
357  const std::vector<std::string> &Values) {
358  switch (OptClass) {
359  case Option::CommaJoinedClass: {
360  std::string CommaJoinedValue;
361  if (!Values.empty()) {
362  CommaJoinedValue.append(Values.front());
363  for (const std::string &Value : llvm::drop_begin(Values, 1)) {
364  CommaJoinedValue.append(",");
365  CommaJoinedValue.append(Value);
366  }
367  }
368  denormalizeString(Args, Spelling, SA, Option::OptionClass::JoinedClass,
369  TableIndex, CommaJoinedValue);
370  break;
371  }
372  case Option::JoinedClass:
373  case Option::SeparateClass:
374  case Option::JoinedOrSeparateClass:
375  for (const std::string &Value : Values)
376  denormalizeString(Args, Spelling, SA, OptClass, TableIndex, Value);
377  break;
378  default:
379  llvm_unreachable("Cannot denormalize an option with option class "
380  "incompatible with string vector denormalization.");
381  }
382 }

411 #define PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
412  ARGS, DIAGS, ID, FLAGS, PARAM, SHOULD_PARSE, KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE, \
413  IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, MERGER, TABLE_INDEX) \
414  if ((FLAGS)&options::CC1Option) { \
415  KEYPATH = MERGER(KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE); \
416  if (IMPLIED_CHECK) \
417  KEYPATH = MERGER(KEYPATH, IMPLIED_VALUE); \
418  if (SHOULD_PARSE) \
419  if (auto MaybeValue = NORMALIZER(OPT_##ID, TABLE_INDEX, ARGS, DIAGS)) \
420  KEYPATH = \
421  MERGER(KEYPATH, static_cast<decltype(KEYPATH)>(*MaybeValue)); \
422  }
423 
424 // Capture the extracted value as a lambda argument to avoid potential issues
425 // with lifetime extension of the reference.
426 #define GENERATE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
427  ARGS, STRING_ALLOCATOR, KIND, FLAGS, SPELLING, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, \
428  DEFAULT_VALUE, IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, DENORMALIZER, EXTRACTOR, \
429  TABLE_INDEX) \
430  if ((FLAGS)&options::CC1Option) { \
431  [&](const auto &Extracted) { \
432  if (ALWAYS_EMIT || \
433  (Extracted != \
434  static_cast<decltype(KEYPATH)>((IMPLIED_CHECK) ? (IMPLIED_VALUE) \
435  : (DEFAULT_VALUE)))) \
436  DENORMALIZER(ARGS, SPELLING, STRING_ALLOCATOR, Option::KIND##Class, \
437  TABLE_INDEX, Extracted); \
438  }(EXTRACTOR(KEYPATH)); \
439  }

443 static bool FixupInvocation(CompilerInvocation &Invocation,
444  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags, const ArgList &Args,
445  InputKind IK) {
446  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
447 
448  LangOptions &LangOpts = *Invocation.getLangOpts();
449  CodeGenOptions &CodeGenOpts = Invocation.getCodeGenOpts();
450  TargetOptions &TargetOpts = Invocation.getTargetOpts();
451  FrontendOptions &FrontendOpts = Invocation.getFrontendOpts();
452  CodeGenOpts.XRayInstrumentFunctions = LangOpts.XRayInstrument;
453  CodeGenOpts.XRayAlwaysEmitCustomEvents = LangOpts.XRayAlwaysEmitCustomEvents;
454  CodeGenOpts.XRayAlwaysEmitTypedEvents = LangOpts.XRayAlwaysEmitTypedEvents;
455  CodeGenOpts.DisableFree = FrontendOpts.DisableFree;
456  FrontendOpts.GenerateGlobalModuleIndex = FrontendOpts.UseGlobalModuleIndex;
457  if (FrontendOpts.ShowStats)
458  CodeGenOpts.ClearASTBeforeBackend = false;
459  LangOpts.SanitizeCoverage = CodeGenOpts.hasSanitizeCoverage();
460  LangOpts.ForceEmitVTables = CodeGenOpts.ForceEmitVTables;
461  LangOpts.SpeculativeLoadHardening = CodeGenOpts.SpeculativeLoadHardening;
462  LangOpts.CurrentModule = LangOpts.ModuleName;
463 
464  llvm::Triple T(TargetOpts.Triple);
465  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch = T.getArch();
466 
467  CodeGenOpts.CodeModel = TargetOpts.CodeModel;
468 
469  if (LangOpts.getExceptionHandling() !=
470  LangOptions::ExceptionHandlingKind::None &&
471  T.isWindowsMSVCEnvironment())
472  Diags.Report(diag::err_fe_invalid_exception_model)
473  << static_cast<unsigned>(LangOpts.getExceptionHandling()) << T.str();
474 
475  if (LangOpts.AppleKext && !LangOpts.CPlusPlus)
476  Diags.Report(diag::warn_c_kext);
477 
478  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fconcepts_ts))
479  Diags.Report(diag::warn_fe_concepts_ts_flag);
480 
481  if (LangOpts.NewAlignOverride &&
482  !llvm::isPowerOf2_32(LangOpts.NewAlignOverride)) {
483  Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_fnew_alignment_EQ);
484  Diags.Report(diag::err_fe_invalid_alignment)
485  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
486  LangOpts.NewAlignOverride = 0;
487  }
488 
489  // Prevent the user from specifying both -fsycl-is-device and -fsycl-is-host.
490  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && LangOpts.SYCLIsHost)
491  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with) << "-fsycl-is-device"
492  << "-fsycl-is-host";
493 
494  // SYCLEnableIntHeader implies SYCLIsHost. Error if
495  // -fsycl-enable-int-header-diags is passed without -fsycl-is-host.
496  if (LangOpts.SYCLEnableIntHeaderDiags && !LangOpts.SYCLIsHost)
497  Diags.Report(diag::err_opt_not_valid_without_opt)
498  << "-fsycl-enable-int-header-diags"
499  << "-fsycl-is-host";
500 
501  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fgnu89_inline) && LangOpts.CPlusPlus)
502  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
503  << "-fgnu89-inline" << GetInputKindName(IK);
504 
505  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fgpu_allow_device_init) && !LangOpts.HIP)
506  Diags.Report(diag::warn_ignored_hip_only_option)
507  << Args.getLastArg(OPT_fgpu_allow_device_init)->getAsString(Args);
508 
509  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_gpu_max_threads_per_block_EQ) && !LangOpts.HIP)
510  Diags.Report(diag::warn_ignored_hip_only_option)
511  << Args.getLastArg(OPT_gpu_max_threads_per_block_EQ)->getAsString(Args);
512 
513  // -cl-strict-aliasing needs to emit diagnostic in the case where CL > 1.0.
514  // This option should be deprecated for CL > 1.0 because
515  // this option was added for compatibility with OpenCL 1.0.
516  if (Args.getLastArg(OPT_cl_strict_aliasing) &&
517  (LangOpts.getOpenCLCompatibleVersion() > 100))
518  Diags.Report(diag::warn_option_invalid_ocl_version)
519  << LangOpts.getOpenCLVersionString()
520  << Args.getLastArg(OPT_cl_strict_aliasing)->getAsString(Args);
521 
522  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_fdefault_calling_conv_EQ)) {
523  auto DefaultCC = LangOpts.getDefaultCallingConv();
524 
525  bool emitError = (DefaultCC == LangOptions::DCC_FastCall ||
526  DefaultCC == LangOptions::DCC_StdCall) &&
527  Arch != llvm::Triple::x86;
528  emitError |= (DefaultCC == LangOptions::DCC_VectorCall ||
529  DefaultCC == LangOptions::DCC_RegCall) &&
530  !T.isX86();
531  if (emitError)
532  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
533  << A->getSpelling() << T.getTriple();
534  }
535 
536  if (!CodeGenOpts.ProfileRemappingFile.empty() && CodeGenOpts.LegacyPassManager)
537  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with)
538  << Args.getLastArg(OPT_fprofile_remapping_file_EQ)->getAsString(Args)
539  << "-fno-legacy-pass-manager";
540 
541  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
542 }

548 static unsigned getOptimizationLevel(ArgList &Args, InputKind IK,
549  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
550  unsigned DefaultOpt = llvm::CodeGenOpt::None;
551  if (((IK.getLanguage() == Language::OpenCL ||
552  IK.getLanguage() == Language::OpenCLCXX) &&
553  !Args.hasArg(OPT_cl_opt_disable)) ||
554  Args.hasArg(OPT_fsycl_is_device))
555  DefaultOpt = llvm::CodeGenOpt::Default;
556 
557  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_O_Group)) {
558  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_O0))
559  return llvm::CodeGenOpt::None;
560 
561  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Ofast))
562  return llvm::CodeGenOpt::Aggressive;
563 
564  assert(A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_O));
565 
566  StringRef S(A->getValue());
567  if (S == "s" || S == "z")
568  return llvm::CodeGenOpt::Default;
569 
570  if (S == "g")
571  return llvm::CodeGenOpt::Less;
572 
573  return getLastArgIntValue(Args, OPT_O, DefaultOpt, Diags);
574  }
575 
576  return DefaultOpt;
577 }

579 static unsigned getOptimizationLevelSize(ArgList &Args) {
580  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_O_Group)) {
581  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_O)) {
582  switch (A->getValue()[0]) {
583  default:
584  return 0;
585  case 's':
586  return 1;
587  case 'z':
588  return 2;
589  }
590  }
591  }
592  return 0;
593 }

612 // Parse command line arguments into CompilerInvocation.
613 using ParseFn =
614  llvm::function_ref<bool(CompilerInvocation &, ArrayRef<const char *>,
615  DiagnosticsEngine &, const char *)>;
616 
617 // Generate command line arguments from CompilerInvocation.
618 using GenerateFn = llvm::function_ref<void(
619  CompilerInvocation &, SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &,
620  CompilerInvocation::StringAllocator)>;
621 
622 // May perform round-trip of command line arguments. By default, the round-trip
623 // is enabled in assert builds. This can be overwritten at run-time via the
624 // "-round-trip-args" and "-no-round-trip-args" command line flags.
625 // During round-trip, the command line arguments are parsed into a dummy
626 // instance of CompilerInvocation which is used to generate the command line
627 // arguments again. The real CompilerInvocation instance is then created by
628 // parsing the generated arguments, not the original ones.
629 static bool RoundTrip(ParseFn Parse, GenerateFn Generate,
630  CompilerInvocation &RealInvocation,
631  CompilerInvocation &DummyInvocation,
632  ArrayRef<const char *> CommandLineArgs,
633  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags, const char *Argv0) {
634 #ifndef NDEBUG
635  bool DoRoundTripDefault = true;
636 #else
637  bool DoRoundTripDefault = false;
638 #endif
639 
640  bool DoRoundTrip = DoRoundTripDefault;
641  for (const auto *Arg : CommandLineArgs) {
642  if (Arg == StringRef("-round-trip-args"))
643  DoRoundTrip = true;
644  if (Arg == StringRef("-no-round-trip-args"))
645  DoRoundTrip = false;
646  }
647 
648  // If round-trip was not requested, simply run the parser with the real
649  // invocation diagnostics.
650  if (!DoRoundTrip)
651  return Parse(RealInvocation, CommandLineArgs, Diags, Argv0);
652 
653  // Serializes quoted (and potentially escaped) arguments.
654  auto SerializeArgs = [](ArrayRef<const char *> Args) {
655  std::string Buffer;
656  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Buffer);
657  for (const char *Arg : Args) {
658  llvm::sys::printArg(OS, Arg, /*Quote=*/true);
659  OS << ' ';
660  }
661  OS.flush();
662  return Buffer;
663  };
664 
665  // Setup a dummy DiagnosticsEngine.
666  DiagnosticsEngine DummyDiags(new DiagnosticIDs(), new DiagnosticOptions());
667  DummyDiags.setClient(new TextDiagnosticBuffer());
668 
669  // Run the first parse on the original arguments with the dummy invocation and
670  // diagnostics.
671  if (!Parse(DummyInvocation, CommandLineArgs, DummyDiags, Argv0) ||
672  DummyDiags.getNumWarnings() != 0) {
673  // If the first parse did not succeed, it must be user mistake (invalid
674  // command line arguments). We won't be able to generate arguments that
675  // would reproduce the same result. Let's fail again with the real
676  // invocation and diagnostics, so all side-effects of parsing are visible.
677  unsigned NumWarningsBefore = Diags.getNumWarnings();
678  auto Success = Parse(RealInvocation, CommandLineArgs, Diags, Argv0);
679  if (!Success || Diags.getNumWarnings() != NumWarningsBefore)
680  return Success;
681 
682  // Parse with original options and diagnostics succeeded even though it
683  // shouldn't have. Something is off.
684  Diags.Report(diag::err_cc1_round_trip_fail_then_ok);
685  Diags.Report(diag::note_cc1_round_trip_original)
686  << SerializeArgs(CommandLineArgs);
687  return false;
688  }
689 
690  // Setup string allocator.
691  llvm::BumpPtrAllocator Alloc;
692  llvm::StringSaver StringPool(Alloc);
693  auto SA = [&StringPool](const Twine &Arg) {
694  return StringPool.save(Arg).data();
695  };
696 
697  // Generate arguments from the dummy invocation. If Generate is the
698  // inverse of Parse, the newly generated arguments must have the same
699  // semantics as the original.
700  SmallVector<const char *> GeneratedArgs1;
701  Generate(DummyInvocation, GeneratedArgs1, SA);
702 
703  // Run the second parse, now on the generated arguments, and with the real
704  // invocation and diagnostics. The result is what we will end up using for the
705  // rest of compilation, so if Generate is not inverse of Parse, something down
706  // the line will break.
707  bool Success2 = Parse(RealInvocation, GeneratedArgs1, Diags, Argv0);
708 
709  // The first parse on original arguments succeeded, but second parse of
710  // generated arguments failed. Something must be wrong with the generator.
711  if (!Success2) {
712  Diags.Report(diag::err_cc1_round_trip_ok_then_fail);
713  Diags.Report(diag::note_cc1_round_trip_generated)
714  << 1 << SerializeArgs(GeneratedArgs1);
715  return false;
716  }
717 
718  // Generate arguments again, this time from the options we will end up using
719  // for the rest of the compilation.
720  SmallVector<const char *> GeneratedArgs2;
721  Generate(RealInvocation, GeneratedArgs2, SA);
722 
723  // Compares two lists of generated arguments.
724  auto Equal = [](const ArrayRef<const char *> A,
725  const ArrayRef<const char *> B) {
726  return std::equal(A.begin(), A.end(), B.begin(), B.end(),
727  [](const char *AElem, const char *BElem) {
728  return StringRef(AElem) == StringRef(BElem);
729  });
730  };
731 
732  // If we generated different arguments from what we assume are two
733  // semantically equivalent CompilerInvocations, the Generate function may
734  // be non-deterministic.
735  if (!Equal(GeneratedArgs1, GeneratedArgs2)) {
736  Diags.Report(diag::err_cc1_round_trip_mismatch);
737  Diags.Report(diag::note_cc1_round_trip_generated)
738  << 1 << SerializeArgs(GeneratedArgs1);
739  Diags.Report(diag::note_cc1_round_trip_generated)
740  << 2 << SerializeArgs(GeneratedArgs2);
741  return false;
742  }
743 
744  Diags.Report(diag::remark_cc1_round_trip_generated)
745  << 1 << SerializeArgs(GeneratedArgs1);
746  Diags.Report(diag::remark_cc1_round_trip_generated)
747  << 2 << SerializeArgs(GeneratedArgs2);
748 
749  return Success2;
750 }

752 static void addDiagnosticArgs(ArgList &Args, OptSpecifier Group,
753  OptSpecifier GroupWithValue,
754  std::vector<std::string> &Diagnostics) {
755  for (auto *A : Args.filtered(Group)) {
756  if (A->getOption().getKind() == Option::FlagClass) {
757  // The argument is a pure flag (such as OPT_Wall or OPT_Wdeprecated). Add
758  // its name (minus the "W" or "R" at the beginning) to the diagnostics.
759  Diagnostics.push_back(
760  std::string(A->getOption().getName().drop_front(1)));
761  } else if (A->getOption().matches(GroupWithValue)) {
762  // This is -Wfoo= or -Rfoo=, where foo is the name of the diagnostic
763  // group. Add only the group name to the diagnostics.
764  Diagnostics.push_back(
765  std::string(A->getOption().getName().drop_front(1).rtrim("=-")));
766  } else {
767  // Otherwise, add its value (for OPT_W_Joined and similar).
768  Diagnostics.push_back(A->getValue());
769  }
770  }
771 }

785 static void GenerateAnalyzerArgs(AnalyzerOptions &Opts,
786  SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
787  CompilerInvocation::StringAllocator SA) {
788  const AnalyzerOptions *AnalyzerOpts = &Opts;
789 
790 #define ANALYZER_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
791  PREFIX_TYPE, NAME, ID, KIND, GROUP, ALIAS, ALIASARGS, FLAGS, PARAM, \
792  HELPTEXT, METAVAR, VALUES, SPELLING, SHOULD_PARSE, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, \
793  DEFAULT_VALUE, IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, DENORMALIZER, \
794  MERGER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX) \
795  GENERATE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
796  Args, SA, KIND, FLAGS, SPELLING, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE, \
797  IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, DENORMALIZER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX)
798 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
799 #undef ANALYZER_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
800 
801  if (Opts.AnalysisStoreOpt != RegionStoreModel) {
802  switch (Opts.AnalysisStoreOpt) {
803 #define ANALYSIS_STORE(NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC, CREATFN) \
804  case NAME##Model: \
805  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_analyzer_store, CMDFLAG, SA); \
806  break;
807 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/Analyses.def"
808  default:
809  llvm_unreachable("Tried to generate unknown analysis store.");
810  }
811  }
812 
813  if (Opts.AnalysisConstraintsOpt != RangeConstraintsModel) {
814  switch (Opts.AnalysisConstraintsOpt) {
815 #define ANALYSIS_CONSTRAINTS(NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC, CREATFN) \
816  case NAME##Model: \
817  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_analyzer_constraints, CMDFLAG, SA); \
818  break;
819 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/Analyses.def"
820  default:
821  llvm_unreachable("Tried to generate unknown analysis constraint.");
822  }
823  }
824 
825  if (Opts.AnalysisDiagOpt != PD_HTML) {
826  switch (Opts.AnalysisDiagOpt) {
827 #define ANALYSIS_DIAGNOSTICS(NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC, CREATFN) \
828  case PD_##NAME: \
829  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_analyzer_output, CMDFLAG, SA); \
830  break;
831 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/Analyses.def"
832  default:
833  llvm_unreachable("Tried to generate unknown analysis diagnostic client.");
834  }
835  }
836 
837  if (Opts.AnalysisPurgeOpt != PurgeStmt) {
838  switch (Opts.AnalysisPurgeOpt) {
839 #define ANALYSIS_PURGE(NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC) \
840  case NAME: \
841  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_analyzer_purge, CMDFLAG, SA); \
842  break;
843 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/Analyses.def"
844  default:
845  llvm_unreachable("Tried to generate unknown analysis purge mode.");
846  }
847  }
848 
849  if (Opts.InliningMode != NoRedundancy) {
850  switch (Opts.InliningMode) {
851 #define ANALYSIS_INLINING_MODE(NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC) \
852  case NAME: \
853  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_analyzer_inlining_mode, CMDFLAG, SA); \
854  break;
855 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/Analyses.def"
856  default:
857  llvm_unreachable("Tried to generate unknown analysis inlining mode.");
858  }
859  }
860 
861  for (const auto &CP : Opts.CheckersAndPackages) {
862  OptSpecifier Opt =
863  CP.second ? OPT_analyzer_checker : OPT_analyzer_disable_checker;
864  GenerateArg(Args, Opt, CP.first, SA);
865  }
866 
867  AnalyzerOptions ConfigOpts;
868  parseAnalyzerConfigs(ConfigOpts, nullptr);
869 
870  for (const auto &C : Opts.Config) {
871  // Don't generate anything that came from parseAnalyzerConfigs. It would be
872  // redundant and may not be valid on the command line.
873  auto Entry = ConfigOpts.Config.find(C.getKey());
874  if (Entry != ConfigOpts.Config.end() && Entry->getValue() == C.getValue())
875  continue;
876 
877  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_analyzer_config, C.getKey() + "=" + C.getValue(), SA);
878  }
879 
880  // Nothing to generate for FullCompilerInvocation.
881 }

883 static bool ParseAnalyzerArgs(AnalyzerOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
884  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
885  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
886 
887  AnalyzerOptions *AnalyzerOpts = &Opts;
888 
889 #define ANALYZER_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
890  PREFIX_TYPE, NAME, ID, KIND, GROUP, ALIAS, ALIASARGS, FLAGS, PARAM, \
891  HELPTEXT, METAVAR, VALUES, SPELLING, SHOULD_PARSE, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, \
892  DEFAULT_VALUE, IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, DENORMALIZER, \
893  MERGER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX) \
894  PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
895  Args, Diags, ID, FLAGS, PARAM, SHOULD_PARSE, KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE, \
896  IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, MERGER, TABLE_INDEX)
897 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
898 #undef ANALYZER_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
899 
900  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_analyzer_store)) {
901  StringRef Name = A->getValue();
902  AnalysisStores Value = llvm::StringSwitch<AnalysisStores>(Name)
903 #define ANALYSIS_STORE(NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC, CREATFN) \
904  .Case(CMDFLAG, NAME##Model)
905 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/Analyses.def"
906  .Default(NumStores);
907  if (Value == NumStores) {
908  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
909  << A->getAsString(Args) << Name;
910  } else {
911  Opts.AnalysisStoreOpt = Value;
912  }
913  }
914 
915  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_analyzer_constraints)) {
916  StringRef Name = A->getValue();
917  AnalysisConstraints Value = llvm::StringSwitch<AnalysisConstraints>(Name)
918 #define ANALYSIS_CONSTRAINTS(NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC, CREATFN) \
919  .Case(CMDFLAG, NAME##Model)
920 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/Analyses.def"
921  .Default(NumConstraints);
922  if (Value == NumConstraints) {
923  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
924  << A->getAsString(Args) << Name;
925  } else {
926 #ifndef LLVM_WITH_Z3
927  if (Value == AnalysisConstraints::Z3ConstraintsModel) {
928  Diags.Report(diag::err_analyzer_not_built_with_z3);
929  }
930 #endif // LLVM_WITH_Z3
931  Opts.AnalysisConstraintsOpt = Value;
932  }
933  }
934 
935  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_analyzer_output)) {
936  StringRef Name = A->getValue();
937  AnalysisDiagClients Value = llvm::StringSwitch<AnalysisDiagClients>(Name)
938 #define ANALYSIS_DIAGNOSTICS(NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC, CREATFN) \
939  .Case(CMDFLAG, PD_##NAME)
940 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/Analyses.def"
941  .Default(NUM_ANALYSIS_DIAG_CLIENTS);
942  if (Value == NUM_ANALYSIS_DIAG_CLIENTS) {
943  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
944  << A->getAsString(Args) << Name;
945  } else {
946  Opts.AnalysisDiagOpt = Value;
947  }
948  }
949 
950  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_analyzer_purge)) {
951  StringRef Name = A->getValue();
952  AnalysisPurgeMode Value = llvm::StringSwitch<AnalysisPurgeMode>(Name)
953 #define ANALYSIS_PURGE(NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC) \
954  .Case(CMDFLAG, NAME)
955 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/Analyses.def"
956  .Default(NumPurgeModes);
957  if (Value == NumPurgeModes) {
958  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
959  << A->getAsString(Args) << Name;
960  } else {
961  Opts.AnalysisPurgeOpt = Value;
962  }
963  }
964 
965  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_analyzer_inlining_mode)) {
966  StringRef Name = A->getValue();
967  AnalysisInliningMode Value = llvm::StringSwitch<AnalysisInliningMode>(Name)
968 #define ANALYSIS_INLINING_MODE(NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC) \
969  .Case(CMDFLAG, NAME)
970 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/Analyses.def"
971  .Default(NumInliningModes);
972  if (Value == NumInliningModes) {
973  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
974  << A->getAsString(Args) << Name;
975  } else {
976  Opts.InliningMode = Value;
977  }
978  }
979 
980  Opts.CheckersAndPackages.clear();
981  for (const Arg *A :
982  Args.filtered(OPT_analyzer_checker, OPT_analyzer_disable_checker)) {
983  A->claim();
984  bool IsEnabled = A->getOption().getID() == OPT_analyzer_checker;
985  // We can have a list of comma separated checker names, e.g:
986  // '-analyzer-checker=cocoa,unix'
987  StringRef CheckerAndPackageList = A->getValue();
988  SmallVector<StringRef, 16> CheckersAndPackages;
989  CheckerAndPackageList.split(CheckersAndPackages, ",");
990  for (const StringRef &CheckerOrPackage : CheckersAndPackages)
991  Opts.CheckersAndPackages.emplace_back(std::string(CheckerOrPackage),
992  IsEnabled);
993  }
994 
995  // Go through the analyzer configuration options.
996  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_analyzer_config)) {
997 
998  // We can have a list of comma separated config names, e.g:
999  // '-analyzer-config key1=val1,key2=val2'
1000  StringRef configList = A->getValue();
1001  SmallVector<StringRef, 4> configVals;
1002  configList.split(configVals, ",");
1003  for (const auto &configVal : configVals) {
1004  StringRef key, val;
1005  std::tie(key, val) = configVal.split("=");
1006  if (val.empty()) {
1007  Diags.Report(SourceLocation(),
1008  diag::err_analyzer_config_no_value) << configVal;
1009  break;
1010  }
1011  if (val.contains('=')) {
1012  Diags.Report(SourceLocation(),
1013  diag::err_analyzer_config_multiple_values)
1014  << configVal;
1015  break;
1016  }
1017 
1018  // TODO: Check checker options too, possibly in CheckerRegistry.
1019  // Leave unknown non-checker configs unclaimed.
1020  if (!key.contains(":") && Opts.isUnknownAnalyzerConfig(key)) {
1021  if (Opts.ShouldEmitErrorsOnInvalidConfigValue)
1022  Diags.Report(diag::err_analyzer_config_unknown) << key;
1023  continue;
1024  }
1025 
1026  A->claim();
1027  Opts.Config[key] = std::string(val);
1028  }
1029  }
1030 
1031  if (Opts.ShouldEmitErrorsOnInvalidConfigValue)
1032  parseAnalyzerConfigs(Opts, &Diags);
1033  else
1034  parseAnalyzerConfigs(Opts, nullptr);
1035 
1036  llvm::raw_string_ostream os(Opts.FullCompilerInvocation);
1037  for (unsigned i = 0; i < Args.getNumInputArgStrings(); ++i) {
1038  if (i != 0)
1039  os << " ";
1040  os << Args.getArgString(i);
1041  }
1042  os.flush();
1043 
1044  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
1045 }

1053  DiagnosticsEngine *Diags,
1054  StringRef &OptionField, StringRef Name,
1055  StringRef DefaultVal) {
1056  // String options may be known to invalid (e.g. if the expected string is a
1057  // file name, but the file does not exist), those will have to be checked in
1058  // parseConfigs.
1059  OptionField = getStringOption(Config, Name, DefaultVal);

1062 static void initOption(AnalyzerOptions::ConfigTable &Config,
1063  DiagnosticsEngine *Diags,
1064  bool &OptionField, StringRef Name, bool DefaultVal) {
1065  auto PossiblyInvalidVal = llvm::StringSwitch<Optional<bool>>(
1066  getStringOption(Config, Name, (DefaultVal ? "true" : "false")))
1067  .Case("true", true)
1068  .Case("false", false)
1069  .Default(None);
1070 
1071  if (!PossiblyInvalidVal) {
1072  if (Diags)
1073  Diags->Report(diag::err_analyzer_config_invalid_input)
1074  << Name << "a boolean";
1075  else
1076  OptionField = DefaultVal;
1077  } else
1078  OptionField = PossiblyInvalidVal.getValue();
1079 }

1081 static void initOption(AnalyzerOptions::ConfigTable &Config,
1082  DiagnosticsEngine *Diags,
1083  unsigned &OptionField, StringRef Name,
1084  unsigned DefaultVal) {
1085 
1086  OptionField = DefaultVal;
1087  bool HasFailed = getStringOption(Config, Name, std::to_string(DefaultVal))
1088  .getAsInteger(0, OptionField);
1089  if (Diags && HasFailed)
1090  Diags->Report(diag::err_analyzer_config_invalid_input)
1091  << Name << "an unsigned";
1092 }

1094 static void parseAnalyzerConfigs(AnalyzerOptions &AnOpts,
1095  DiagnosticsEngine *Diags) {
1096  // TODO: There's no need to store the entire configtable, it'd be plenty
1097  // enough tostore checker options.
1098 
1099 #define ANALYZER_OPTION(TYPE, NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC, DEFAULT_VAL) \
1100  initOption(AnOpts.Config, Diags, AnOpts.NAME, CMDFLAG, DEFAULT_VAL);
1101 
1102 #define ANALYZER_OPTION_DEPENDS_ON_USER_MODE(TYPE, NAME, CMDFLAG, DESC, \
1103  SHALLOW_VAL, DEEP_VAL) \
1104  switch (AnOpts.getUserMode()) { \
1105  case UMK_Shallow: \
1106  initOption(AnOpts.Config, Diags, AnOpts.NAME, CMDFLAG, SHALLOW_VAL); \
1107  break; \
1108  case UMK_Deep: \
1109  initOption(AnOpts.Config, Diags, AnOpts.NAME, CMDFLAG, DEEP_VAL); \
1110  break; \
1111  } \
1112 
1113 #include "clang/StaticAnalyzer/Core/AnalyzerOptions.def"
1114 #undef ANALYZER_OPTION
1115 #undef ANALYZER_OPTION_DEPENDS_ON_USER_MODE
1116 
1117  // At this point, AnalyzerOptions is configured. Let's validate some options.
1118 
1119  // FIXME: Here we try to validate the silenced checkers or packages are valid.
1120  // The current approach only validates the registered checkers which does not
1121  // contain the runtime enabled checkers and optimally we would validate both.
1122  if (!AnOpts.RawSilencedCheckersAndPackages.empty()) {
1123  std::vector<StringRef> Checkers =
1124  AnOpts.getRegisteredCheckers(/*IncludeExperimental=*/true);
1125  std::vector<StringRef> Packages =
1126  AnOpts.getRegisteredPackages(/*IncludeExperimental=*/true);
1127 
1128  SmallVector<StringRef, 16> CheckersAndPackages;
1129  AnOpts.RawSilencedCheckersAndPackages.split(CheckersAndPackages, ";");
1130 
1131  for (const StringRef &CheckerOrPackage : CheckersAndPackages) {
1132  if (Diags) {
1133  bool IsChecker = CheckerOrPackage.contains('.');
1134  bool IsValidName = IsChecker
1135  ? llvm::is_contained(Checkers, CheckerOrPackage)
1136  : llvm::is_contained(Packages, CheckerOrPackage);
1137 
1138  if (!IsValidName)
1139  Diags->Report(diag::err_unknown_analyzer_checker_or_package)
1140  << CheckerOrPackage;
1141  }
1142 
1143  AnOpts.SilencedCheckersAndPackages.emplace_back(CheckerOrPackage);
1144  }
1145  }
1146 
1147  if (!Diags)
1148  return;
1149 
1150  if (AnOpts.ShouldTrackConditionsDebug && !AnOpts.ShouldTrackConditions)
1151  Diags->Report(diag::err_analyzer_config_invalid_input)

1155  Diags->Report(diag::err_analyzer_config_invalid_input) << "ctu-dir"
1156  << "a filename";
1157 
1158  if (!AnOpts.ModelPath.empty() &&
1159  !llvm::sys::fs::is_directory(AnOpts.ModelPath))
1160  Diags->Report(diag::err_analyzer_config_invalid_input) << "model-path"
1161  << "a filename";

1164 /// Generate a remark argument. This is an inverse of `ParseOptimizationRemark`.
1165 static void
1166 GenerateOptimizationRemark(SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
1167  CompilerInvocation::StringAllocator SA,
1168  OptSpecifier OptEQ, StringRef Name,
1169  const CodeGenOptions::OptRemark &Remark) {
1170  if (Remark.hasValidPattern()) {
1171  GenerateArg(Args, OptEQ, Remark.Pattern, SA);
1172  } else if (Remark.Kind == CodeGenOptions::RK_Enabled) {
1173  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_R_Joined, Name, SA);
1174  } else if (Remark.Kind == CodeGenOptions::RK_Disabled) {
1175  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_R_Joined, StringRef("no-") + Name, SA);
1176  }
1177 }
1178 
1179 /// Parse a remark command line argument. It may be missing, disabled/enabled by
1180 /// '-R[no-]group' or specified with a regular expression by '-Rgroup=regexp'.
1181 /// On top of that, it can be disabled/enabled globally by '-R[no-]everything'.
1182 static CodeGenOptions::OptRemark
1183 ParseOptimizationRemark(DiagnosticsEngine &Diags, ArgList &Args,
1184  OptSpecifier OptEQ, StringRef Name) {
1185  CodeGenOptions::OptRemark Result;
1186 
1187  auto InitializeResultPattern = [&Diags, &Args, &Result](const Arg *A,
1188  StringRef Pattern) {
1189  Result.Pattern = Pattern.str();
1190 
1191  std::string RegexError;
1192  Result.Regex = std::make_shared<llvm::Regex>(Result.Pattern);
1193  if (!Result.Regex->isValid(RegexError)) {
1194  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_optimization_remark_pattern)
1195  << RegexError << A->getAsString(Args);
1196  return false;
1197  }
1198 
1199  return true;
1200  };
1201 
1202  for (Arg *A : Args) {
1203  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_R_Joined)) {
1204  StringRef Value = A->getValue();
1205 
1206  if (Value == Name)
1207  Result.Kind = CodeGenOptions::RK_Enabled;
1208  else if (Value == "everything")
1209  Result.Kind = CodeGenOptions::RK_EnabledEverything;
1210  else if (Value.split('-') == std::make_pair(StringRef("no"), Name))
1211  Result.Kind = CodeGenOptions::RK_Disabled;
1212  else if (Value == "no-everything")
1213  Result.Kind = CodeGenOptions::RK_DisabledEverything;
1214  else
1215  continue;
1216 
1217  if (Result.Kind == CodeGenOptions::RK_Disabled ||
1218  Result.Kind == CodeGenOptions::RK_DisabledEverything) {
1219  Result.Pattern = "";
1220  Result.Regex = nullptr;
1221  } else {
1222  InitializeResultPattern(A, ".*");
1223  }
1224  } else if (A->getOption().matches(OptEQ)) {
1225  Result.Kind = CodeGenOptions::RK_WithPattern;
1226  if (!InitializeResultPattern(A, A->getValue()))
1227  return CodeGenOptions::OptRemark();
1228  }
1229  }
1230 
1231  return Result;
1232 }

1234 static bool parseDiagnosticLevelMask(StringRef FlagName,
1235  const std::vector<std::string> &Levels,
1236  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
1237  DiagnosticLevelMask &M) {
1238  bool Success = true;
1239  for (const auto &Level : Levels) {
1240  DiagnosticLevelMask const PM =
1241  llvm::StringSwitch<DiagnosticLevelMask>(Level)
1242  .Case("note", DiagnosticLevelMask::Note)
1243  .Case("remark", DiagnosticLevelMask::Remark)
1244  .Case("warning", DiagnosticLevelMask::Warning)
1245  .Case("error", DiagnosticLevelMask::Error)
1246  .Default(DiagnosticLevelMask::None);
1247  if (PM == DiagnosticLevelMask::None) {
1248  Success = false;
1249  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << FlagName << Level;
1250  }
1251  M = M | PM;
1252  }
1253  return Success;
1254 }

1256 static void parseSanitizerKinds(StringRef FlagName,
1257  const std::vector<std::string> &Sanitizers,
1258  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags, SanitizerSet &S) {

1261  if (K == SanitizerMask())
1262  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << FlagName << Sanitizer;
1263  else
1264  S.set(K, true);
1265  }
1266 }

1274 static void parseXRayInstrumentationBundle(StringRef FlagName, StringRef Bundle,
1275  ArgList &Args, DiagnosticsEngine &D,
1276  XRayInstrSet &S) {
1277  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 2> BundleParts;
1278  llvm::SplitString(Bundle, BundleParts, ",");
1279  for (const auto &B : BundleParts) {
1280  auto Mask = parseXRayInstrValue(B);
1281  if (Mask == XRayInstrKind::None)
1282  if (B != "none")
1283  D.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << FlagName << Bundle;
1284  else
1285  S.Mask = Mask;
1286  else if (Mask == XRayInstrKind::All)
1287  S.Mask = Mask;
1288  else
1289  S.set(Mask, true);
1290  }
1291 }
1292 
1293 static std::string serializeXRayInstrumentationBundle(const XRayInstrSet &S) {
1294  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 2> BundleParts;
1295  serializeXRayInstrValue(S, BundleParts);
1296  std::string Buffer;
1297  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Buffer);
1298  llvm::interleave(BundleParts, OS, [&OS](StringRef Part) { OS << Part; }, ",");
1299  return Buffer;
1300 }

1302 // Set the profile kind using fprofile-instrument-use-path.
1303 static void setPGOUseInstrumentor(CodeGenOptions &Opts,
1304  const Twine &ProfileName) {
1305  auto ReaderOrErr = llvm::IndexedInstrProfReader::create(ProfileName);
1306  // In error, return silently and let Clang PGOUse report the error message.
1307  if (auto E = ReaderOrErr.takeError()) {
1308  llvm::consumeError(std::move(E));
1309  Opts.setProfileUse(CodeGenOptions::ProfileClangInstr);
1310  return;
1311  }
1312  std::unique_ptr<llvm::IndexedInstrProfReader> PGOReader =
1313  std::move(ReaderOrErr.get());
1314  if (PGOReader->isIRLevelProfile()) {
1315  if (PGOReader->hasCSIRLevelProfile())
1316  Opts.setProfileUse(CodeGenOptions::ProfileCSIRInstr);
1317  else
1318  Opts.setProfileUse(CodeGenOptions::ProfileIRInstr);
1319  } else
1320  Opts.setProfileUse(CodeGenOptions::ProfileClangInstr);
1321 }

1567 bool CompilerInvocation::ParseCodeGenArgs(CodeGenOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
1568  InputKind IK,
1569  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
1570  const llvm::Triple &T,
1571  const std::string &OutputFile,
1572  const LangOptions &LangOptsRef) {
1573  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
1574 
1575  unsigned OptimizationLevel = getOptimizationLevel(Args, IK, Diags);
1576  // TODO: This could be done in Driver
1577  unsigned MaxOptLevel = 3;
1578  if (OptimizationLevel > MaxOptLevel) {
1579  // If the optimization level is not supported, fall back on the default
1580  // optimization
1581  Diags.Report(diag::warn_drv_optimization_value)
1582  << Args.getLastArg(OPT_O)->getAsString(Args) << "-O" << MaxOptLevel;
1583  OptimizationLevel = MaxOptLevel;
1584  }
1585  Opts.OptimizationLevel = OptimizationLevel;
1586 
1587  // The key paths of codegen options defined in Options.td start with
1588  // "CodeGenOpts.". Let's provide the expected variable name and type.
1589  CodeGenOptions &CodeGenOpts = Opts;
1590  // Some codegen options depend on language options. Let's provide the expected
1591  // variable name and type.
1592  const LangOptions *LangOpts = &LangOptsRef;
1593 
1594 #define CODEGEN_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
1595  PREFIX_TYPE, NAME, ID, KIND, GROUP, ALIAS, ALIASARGS, FLAGS, PARAM, \
1596  HELPTEXT, METAVAR, VALUES, SPELLING, SHOULD_PARSE, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, \
1597  DEFAULT_VALUE, IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, DENORMALIZER, \
1598  MERGER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX) \
1599  PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
1600  Args, Diags, ID, FLAGS, PARAM, SHOULD_PARSE, KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE, \
1601  IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, MERGER, TABLE_INDEX)
1602 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
1603 #undef CODEGEN_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
1604 
1605  // At O0 we want to fully disable inlining outside of cases marked with
1606  // 'alwaysinline' that are required for correctness.
1607  Opts.setInlining((Opts.OptimizationLevel == 0)
1608  ? CodeGenOptions::OnlyAlwaysInlining
1609  : CodeGenOptions::NormalInlining);
1610  // Explicit inlining flags can disable some or all inlining even at
1611  // optimization levels above zero.
1612  if (Arg *InlineArg = Args.getLastArg(
1613  options::OPT_finline_functions, options::OPT_finline_hint_functions,
1614  options::OPT_fno_inline_functions, options::OPT_fno_inline)) {
1615  if (Opts.OptimizationLevel > 0) {
1616  const Option &InlineOpt = InlineArg->getOption();
1617  if (InlineOpt.matches(options::OPT_finline_functions))
1618  Opts.setInlining(CodeGenOptions::NormalInlining);
1619  else if (InlineOpt.matches(options::OPT_finline_hint_functions))
1620  Opts.setInlining(CodeGenOptions::OnlyHintInlining);
1621  else
1622  Opts.setInlining(CodeGenOptions::OnlyAlwaysInlining);
1623  }
1624  }
1625 
1626  // PIC defaults to -fno-direct-access-external-data while non-PIC defaults to
1627  // -fdirect-access-external-data.
1628  Opts.DirectAccessExternalData =
1629  Args.hasArg(OPT_fdirect_access_external_data) ||
1630  (!Args.hasArg(OPT_fno_direct_access_external_data) &&
1631  LangOpts->PICLevel == 0);
1632 
1633  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_debug_info_kind_EQ)) {
1634  unsigned Val =
1635  llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(A->getValue())
1636  .Case("line-tables-only", codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
1637  .Case("line-directives-only", codegenoptions::DebugDirectivesOnly)
1638  .Case("constructor", codegenoptions::DebugInfoConstructor)
1639  .Case("limited", codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo)
1640  .Case("standalone", codegenoptions::FullDebugInfo)
1641  .Case("unused-types", codegenoptions::UnusedTypeInfo)
1642  .Default(~0U);
1643  if (Val == ~0U)
1644  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getAsString(Args)
1645  << A->getValue();
1646  else
1647  Opts.setDebugInfo(static_cast<codegenoptions::DebugInfoKind>(Val));
1648  }
1649 
1650  // If -fuse-ctor-homing is set and limited debug info is already on, then use
1651  // constructor homing, and vice versa for -fno-use-ctor-homing.
1652  if (const Arg *A =
1653  Args.getLastArg(OPT_fuse_ctor_homing, OPT_fno_use_ctor_homing)) {
1654  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_fuse_ctor_homing) &&
1655  Opts.getDebugInfo() == codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo)
1656  Opts.setDebugInfo(codegenoptions::DebugInfoConstructor);
1657  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_fno_use_ctor_homing) &&
1658  Opts.getDebugInfo() == codegenoptions::DebugInfoConstructor)
1659  Opts.setDebugInfo(codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo);
1660  }
1661 
1662  for (const auto &Arg : Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_fdebug_prefix_map_EQ)) {
1663  auto Split = StringRef(Arg).split('=');
1664  Opts.DebugPrefixMap.insert(
1665  {std::string(Split.first), std::string(Split.second)});

2013 static void
2014 GenerateDependencyOutputArgs(const DependencyOutputOptions &Opts,
2015  SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
2016  CompilerInvocation::StringAllocator SA) {
2017  const DependencyOutputOptions &DependencyOutputOpts = Opts;
2018 #define DEPENDENCY_OUTPUT_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
2019  PREFIX_TYPE, NAME, ID, KIND, GROUP, ALIAS, ALIASARGS, FLAGS, PARAM, \
2020  HELPTEXT, METAVAR, VALUES, SPELLING, SHOULD_PARSE, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, \
2021  DEFAULT_VALUE, IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, DENORMALIZER, \
2022  MERGER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX) \
2023  GENERATE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
2024  Args, SA, KIND, FLAGS, SPELLING, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE, \
2025  IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, DENORMALIZER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX)
2026 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
2027 #undef DEPENDENCY_OUTPUT_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
2028 
2029  if (Opts.ShowIncludesDest != ShowIncludesDestination::None)
2030  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_show_includes, SA);
2031 
2032  for (const auto &Dep : Opts.ExtraDeps) {
2033  switch (Dep.second) {
2034  case EDK_SanitizeIgnorelist:
2035  // Sanitizer ignorelist arguments are generated from LanguageOptions.
2036  continue;
2037  case EDK_ModuleFile:
2038  // Module file arguments are generated from FrontendOptions and
2039  // HeaderSearchOptions.
2040  continue;
2041  case EDK_ProfileList:
2042  // Profile list arguments are generated from LanguageOptions via the
2043  // marshalling infrastructure.
2044  continue;
2045  case EDK_DepFileEntry:
2046  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_fdepfile_entry, Dep.first, SA);
2047  break;
2048  }
2049  }
2050 }

2052 static bool ParseDependencyOutputArgs(DependencyOutputOptions &Opts,
2053  ArgList &Args, DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
2054  frontend::ActionKind Action,
2055  bool ShowLineMarkers) {
2056  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
2057 
2058  DependencyOutputOptions &DependencyOutputOpts = Opts;
2059 #define DEPENDENCY_OUTPUT_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
2060  PREFIX_TYPE, NAME, ID, KIND, GROUP, ALIAS, ALIASARGS, FLAGS, PARAM, \
2061  HELPTEXT, METAVAR, VALUES, SPELLING, SHOULD_PARSE, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, \
2062  DEFAULT_VALUE, IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, DENORMALIZER, \
2063  MERGER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX) \
2064  PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
2065  Args, Diags, ID, FLAGS, PARAM, SHOULD_PARSE, KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE, \
2066  IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, MERGER, TABLE_INDEX)
2067 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
2068 #undef DEPENDENCY_OUTPUT_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
2069 
2070  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_show_includes)) {
2071  // Writing both /showIncludes and preprocessor output to stdout
2072  // would produce interleaved output, so use stderr for /showIncludes.
2073  // This behaves the same as cl.exe, when /E, /EP or /P are passed.
2074  if (Action == frontend::PrintPreprocessedInput || !ShowLineMarkers)
2075  Opts.ShowIncludesDest = ShowIncludesDestination::Stderr;
2076  else
2077  Opts.ShowIncludesDest = ShowIncludesDestination::Stdout;
2078  } else {
2079  Opts.ShowIncludesDest = ShowIncludesDestination::None;
2080  }
2081 
2082  // Add sanitizer ignorelists as extra dependencies.
2083  // They won't be discovered by the regular preprocessor, so
2084  // we let make / ninja to know about this implicit dependency.
2085  if (!Args.hasArg(OPT_fno_sanitize_ignorelist)) {
2086  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fsanitize_ignorelist_EQ)) {
2087  StringRef Val = A->getValue();
2088  if (!Val.contains('='))
2089  Opts.ExtraDeps.emplace_back(std::string(Val), EDK_SanitizeIgnorelist);
2090  }
2091  if (Opts.IncludeSystemHeaders) {
2092  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fsanitize_system_ignorelist_EQ)) {
2093  StringRef Val = A->getValue();
2094  if (!Val.contains('='))
2095  Opts.ExtraDeps.emplace_back(std::string(Val), EDK_SanitizeIgnorelist);
2096  }
2097  }
2098  }
2099 
2100  // -fprofile-list= dependencies.
2101  for (const auto &Filename : Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_fprofile_list_EQ))
2102  Opts.ExtraDeps.emplace_back(Filename, EDK_ProfileList);
2103 
2104  // Propagate the extra dependencies.
2105  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fdepfile_entry))
2106  Opts.ExtraDeps.emplace_back(A->getValue(), EDK_DepFileEntry);
2107 
2108  // Only the -fmodule-file=<file> form.
2109  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fmodule_file)) {
2110  StringRef Val = A->getValue();
2111  if (!Val.contains('='))
2112  Opts.ExtraDeps.emplace_back(std::string(Val), EDK_ModuleFile);
2113  }
2114 
2115  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
2116 }

2118 static bool parseShowColorsArgs(const ArgList &Args, bool DefaultColor) {
2119  // Color diagnostics default to auto ("on" if terminal supports) in the driver
2120  // but default to off in cc1, needing an explicit OPT_fdiagnostics_color.
2121  // Support both clang's -f[no-]color-diagnostics and gcc's
2122  // -f[no-]diagnostics-colors[=never|always|auto].
2123  enum {
2124  Colors_On,
2125  Colors_Off,
2126  Colors_Auto
2127  } ShowColors = DefaultColor ? Colors_Auto : Colors_Off;
2128  for (auto *A : Args) {
2129  const Option &O = A->getOption();
2130  if (O.matches(options::OPT_fcolor_diagnostics) ||
2131  O.matches(options::OPT_fdiagnostics_color)) {
2132  ShowColors = Colors_On;
2133  } else if (O.matches(options::OPT_fno_color_diagnostics) ||
2134  O.matches(options::OPT_fno_diagnostics_color)) {
2135  ShowColors = Colors_Off;
2136  } else if (O.matches(options::OPT_fdiagnostics_color_EQ)) {
2137  StringRef Value(A->getValue());
2138  if (Value == "always")
2139  ShowColors = Colors_On;
2140  else if (Value == "never")
2141  ShowColors = Colors_Off;
2142  else if (Value == "auto")
2143  ShowColors = Colors_Auto;
2144  }
2145  }
2146  return ShowColors == Colors_On ||
2147  (ShowColors == Colors_Auto &&
2148  llvm::sys::Process::StandardErrHasColors());
2149 }

2151 static bool checkVerifyPrefixes(const std::vector<std::string> &VerifyPrefixes,
2152  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
2153  bool Success = true;
2154  for (const auto &Prefix : VerifyPrefixes) {
2155  // Every prefix must start with a letter and contain only alphanumeric
2156  // characters, hyphens, and underscores.
2157  auto BadChar = llvm::find_if(Prefix, [](char C) {
2158  return !isAlphanumeric(C) && C != '-' && C != '_';
2159  });
2160  if (BadChar != Prefix.end() || !isLetter(Prefix[0])) {
2161  Success = false;
2162  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << "-verify=" << Prefix;
2163  Diags.Report(diag::note_drv_verify_prefix_spelling);
2164  }

2256 
2257  if (!Opts.DiagnosticSerializationFile.empty())
2258  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_diagnostic_serialized_file,
2259  Opts.DiagnosticSerializationFile, SA);
2260 
2261  if (Opts.ShowColors)
2262  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_fcolor_diagnostics, SA);
2263

2667  unsigned Val = llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(A->getValue())
2668  .CaseLower("default", ADOF_Default)
2669  .CaseLower("json", ADOF_JSON)
2670  .Default(std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max());
2671 
2672  if (Val != std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max())
2673  Opts.ASTDumpFormat = static_cast<ASTDumpOutputFormat>(Val);
2674  else {
2675  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
2676  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
2677  Opts.ASTDumpFormat = ADOF_Default;
2678  }
2679  }
2680 
2681  if (ProgramAction == frontend::FixIt && Opt == OPT_fixit_EQ)
2682  Opts.FixItSuffix = A->getValue();
2683 
2684  if (ProgramAction == frontend::GenerateInterfaceStubs) {
2685  StringRef ArgStr =
2686  Args.hasArg(OPT_interface_stub_version_EQ)
2687  ? Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_interface_stub_version_EQ)
2688  : "ifs-v1";
2689  if (ArgStr == "experimental-yaml-elf-v1" ||
2690  ArgStr == "experimental-ifs-v1" || ArgStr == "experimental-ifs-v2" ||
2691  ArgStr == "experimental-tapi-elf-v1") {
2692  std::string ErrorMessage =
2693  "Invalid interface stub format: " + ArgStr.str() +
2694  " is deprecated.";
2695  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
2696  << "Must specify a valid interface stub format type, ie: "
2697  "-interface-stub-version=ifs-v1"
2698  << ErrorMessage;
2699  ProgramAction = frontend::ParseSyntaxOnly;
2700  } else if (!ArgStr.startswith("ifs-")) {
2701  std::string ErrorMessage =
2702  "Invalid interface stub format: " + ArgStr.str() + ".";
2703  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
2704  << "Must specify a valid interface stub format type, ie: "
2705  "-interface-stub-version=ifs-v1"
2706  << ErrorMessage;
2707  ProgramAction = frontend::ParseSyntaxOnly;
2708  }
2709  }
2710 
2711  Opts.ProgramAction = *ProgramAction;
2712  }
2713 
2714  if (const Arg* A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_plugin)) {
2715  Opts.Plugins.emplace_back(A->getValue(0));
2716  Opts.ProgramAction = frontend::PluginAction;
2717  Opts.ActionName = A->getValue();
2718  }
2719  for (const auto *AA : Args.filtered(OPT_plugin_arg))
2720  Opts.PluginArgs[AA->getValue(0)].emplace_back(AA->getValue(1));
2721 
2722  for (const std::string &Arg :
2723  Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_ftest_module_file_extension_EQ)) {
2724  std::string BlockName;
2725  unsigned MajorVersion;
2726  unsigned MinorVersion;
2727  bool Hashed;
2728  std::string UserInfo;
2729  if (parseTestModuleFileExtensionArg(Arg, BlockName, MajorVersion,
2730  MinorVersion, Hashed, UserInfo)) {
2731  Diags.Report(diag::err_test_module_file_extension_format) << Arg;
2732 
2733  continue;
2734  }
2735 
2736  // Add the testing module file extension.
2737  Opts.ModuleFileExtensions.push_back(
2738  std::make_shared<TestModuleFileExtension>(
2739  BlockName, MajorVersion, MinorVersion, Hashed, UserInfo));
2740  }
2741 
2742  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_code_completion_at)) {
2743  Opts.CodeCompletionAt =
2744  ParsedSourceLocation::FromString(A->getValue());
2745  if (Opts.CodeCompletionAt.FileName.empty())
2746  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
2747  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
2748  }
2749 
2750  Opts.Plugins = Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_load);
2751  Opts.ASTDumpDecls = Args.hasArg(OPT_ast_dump, OPT_ast_dump_EQ);
2752  Opts.ASTDumpAll = Args.hasArg(OPT_ast_dump_all, OPT_ast_dump_all_EQ);
2753  // Only the -fmodule-file=<file> form.
2754  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fmodule_file)) {
2755  StringRef Val = A->getValue();
2756  if (!Val.contains('='))
2757  Opts.ModuleFiles.push_back(std::string(Val));
2758  }
2759 
2760  if (Opts.ProgramAction != frontend::GenerateModule && Opts.IsSystemModule)
2761  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with) << "-fsystem-module"
2762  << "-emit-module";
2763 
2764  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_aux_target_cpu))
2765  Opts.AuxTargetCPU = std::string(Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_aux_target_cpu));
2766  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_aux_target_feature))
2767  Opts.AuxTargetFeatures = Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_aux_target_feature);
2768 
2769  if (Opts.ARCMTAction != FrontendOptions::ARCMT_None &&
2770  Opts.ObjCMTAction != FrontendOptions::ObjCMT_None) {
2771  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
2772  << "ARC migration" << "ObjC migration";
2773  }
2774 
2775  InputKind DashX(Language::Unknown);
2776  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_x)) {
2777  StringRef XValue = A->getValue();
2778 
2779  // Parse suffixes: '<lang>(-header|[-module-map][-cpp-output])'.
2780  // FIXME: Supporting '<lang>-header-cpp-output' would be useful.
2781  bool Preprocessed = XValue.consume_back("-cpp-output");
2782  bool ModuleMap = XValue.consume_back("-module-map");
2783  IsHeaderFile = !Preprocessed && !ModuleMap &&
2784  XValue != "precompiled-header" &&
2785  XValue.consume_back("-header");
2786 
2787  // Principal languages.
2788  DashX = llvm::StringSwitch<InputKind>(XValue)
2789  .Case("c", Language::C)
2790  .Case("cl", Language::OpenCL)
2791  .Case("clcpp", Language::OpenCLCXX)
2792  .Case("cuda", Language::CUDA)
2793  .Case("hip", Language::HIP)
2794  .Case("c++", Language::CXX)
2795  .Case("objective-c", Language::ObjC)
2796  .Case("objective-c++", Language::ObjCXX)
2797  .Case("renderscript", Language::RenderScript)
2798  .Default(Language::Unknown);
2799 
2800  // "objc[++]-cpp-output" is an acceptable synonym for
2801  // "objective-c[++]-cpp-output".
2802  if (DashX.isUnknown() && Preprocessed && !IsHeaderFile && !ModuleMap)
2803  DashX = llvm::StringSwitch<InputKind>(XValue)
2804  .Case("objc", Language::ObjC)
2805  .Case("objc++", Language::ObjCXX)
2806  .Default(Language::Unknown);
2807 
2808  // Some special cases cannot be combined with suffixes.
2809  if (DashX.isUnknown() && !Preprocessed && !ModuleMap && !IsHeaderFile)
2810  DashX = llvm::StringSwitch<InputKind>(XValue)
2811  .Case("cpp-output", InputKind(Language::C).getPreprocessed())
2812  .Case("assembler-with-cpp", Language::Asm)
2813  .Cases("ast", "pcm", "precompiled-header",
2814  InputKind(Language::Unknown, InputKind::Precompiled))
2815  .Case("ir", Language::LLVM_IR)
2816  .Default(Language::Unknown);
2817 
2818  if (DashX.isUnknown())
2819  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
2820  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
2821 
2822  if (Preprocessed)
2823  DashX = DashX.getPreprocessed();
2824  if (ModuleMap)
2825  DashX = DashX.withFormat(InputKind::ModuleMap);
2826  }
2827 
2828  // '-' is the default input if none is given.
2829  std::vector<std::string> Inputs = Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_INPUT);
2830  Opts.Inputs.clear();
2831  if (Inputs.empty())
2832  Inputs.push_back("-");
2833  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Inputs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2834  InputKind IK = DashX;
2835  if (IK.isUnknown()) {
2836  IK = FrontendOptions::getInputKindForExtension(
2837  StringRef(Inputs[i]).rsplit('.').second);
2838  // FIXME: Warn on this?
2839  if (IK.isUnknown())
2840  IK = Language::C;
2841  // FIXME: Remove this hack.
2842  if (i == 0)
2843  DashX = IK;
2844  }
2845 
2846  bool IsSystem = false;
2847 
2848  // The -emit-module action implicitly takes a module map.
2849  if (Opts.ProgramAction == frontend::GenerateModule &&
2850  IK.getFormat() == InputKind::Source) {
2851  IK = IK.withFormat(InputKind::ModuleMap);
2852  IsSystem = Opts.IsSystemModule;
2853  }
2854 
2855  Opts.Inputs.emplace_back(std::move(Inputs[i]), IK, IsSystem);
2856  }
2857 
2858  Opts.DashX = DashX;
2859 
2860  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
2861 }

2870 static void GenerateHeaderSearchArgs(HeaderSearchOptions &Opts,
2871  SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
2872  CompilerInvocation::StringAllocator SA) {
2873  const HeaderSearchOptions *HeaderSearchOpts = &Opts;
2874 #define HEADER_SEARCH_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
2875  PREFIX_TYPE, NAME, ID, KIND, GROUP, ALIAS, ALIASARGS, FLAGS, PARAM, \
2876  HELPTEXT, METAVAR, VALUES, SPELLING, SHOULD_PARSE, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, \
2877  DEFAULT_VALUE, IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, DENORMALIZER, \
2878  MERGER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX) \
2879  GENERATE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
2880  Args, SA, KIND, FLAGS, SPELLING, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE, \
2881  IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, DENORMALIZER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX)
2882 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
2883 #undef HEADER_SEARCH_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
2884 
2885  if (Opts.UseLibcxx)
2886  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_stdlib_EQ, "libc++", SA);
2887 
2888  if (!Opts.ModuleCachePath.empty())
2889  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_fmodules_cache_path, Opts.ModuleCachePath, SA);
2890 
2891  for (const auto &File : Opts.PrebuiltModuleFiles)
2892  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_fmodule_file, File.first + "=" + File.second, SA);
2893 
2894  for (const auto &Path : Opts.PrebuiltModulePaths)
2895  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_fprebuilt_module_path, Path, SA);
2896 
2897  for (const auto &Macro : Opts.ModulesIgnoreMacros)
2898  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_fmodules_ignore_macro, Macro.val(), SA);
2899 
2900  auto Matches = [](const HeaderSearchOptions::Entry &Entry,
2901  llvm::ArrayRef<frontend::IncludeDirGroup> Groups,
2902  llvm::Optional<bool> IsFramework,
2903  llvm::Optional<bool> IgnoreSysRoot) {
2904  return llvm::is_contained(Groups, Entry.Group) &&
2905  (!IsFramework || (Entry.IsFramework == *IsFramework)) &&
2906  (!IgnoreSysRoot || (Entry.IgnoreSysRoot == *IgnoreSysRoot));
2907  };
2908 
2909  auto It = Opts.UserEntries.begin();
2910  auto End = Opts.UserEntries.end();
2911 
2912  // Add -I..., -F..., and -index-header-map options in order.
2913  for (; It < End &&
2914  Matches(*It, {frontend::IndexHeaderMap, frontend::Angled}, None, true);
2915  ++It) {
2916  OptSpecifier Opt = [It, Matches]() {
2917  if (Matches(*It, frontend::IndexHeaderMap, true, true))
2918  return OPT_F;
2919  if (Matches(*It, frontend::IndexHeaderMap, false, true))
2920  return OPT_I;
2921  if (Matches(*It, frontend::Angled, true, true))
2922  return OPT_F;
2923  if (Matches(*It, frontend::Angled, false, true))
2924  return OPT_I;
2925  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected HeaderSearchOptions::Entry.");
2926  }();
2927 
2928  if (It->Group == frontend::IndexHeaderMap)
2929  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_index_header_map, SA);
2930  GenerateArg(Args, Opt, It->Path, SA);
2931  };
2932 
2933  // Note: some paths that came from "[-iprefix=xx] -iwithprefixbefore=yy" may
2934  // have already been generated as "-I[xx]yy". If that's the case, their
2935  // position on command line was such that this has no semantic impact on
2936  // include paths.
2937  for (; It < End &&
2938  Matches(*It, {frontend::After, frontend::Angled}, false, true);
2939  ++It) {
2940  OptSpecifier Opt =
2941  It->Group == frontend::After ? OPT_iwithprefix : OPT_iwithprefixbefore;
2942  GenerateArg(Args, Opt, It->Path, SA);
2943  }
2944 
2945  // Note: Some paths that came from "-idirafter=xxyy" may have already been
2946  // generated as "-iwithprefix=xxyy". If that's the case, their position on
2947  // command line was such that this has no semantic impact on include paths.
2948  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::After}, false, true); ++It)
2949  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_idirafter, It->Path, SA);
2950  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::Quoted}, false, true); ++It)
2951  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_iquote, It->Path, SA);
2952  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::System}, false, None); ++It)
2953  GenerateArg(Args, It->IgnoreSysRoot ? OPT_isystem : OPT_iwithsysroot,
2954  It->Path, SA);
2955  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::System}, true, true); ++It)
2956  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_iframework, It->Path, SA);
2957  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::System}, true, false); ++It)
2958  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_iframeworkwithsysroot, It->Path, SA);
2959 
2960  // Add the paths for the various language specific isystem flags.
2961  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::CSystem}, false, true); ++It)
2962  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_c_isystem, It->Path, SA);
2963  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::CXXSystem}, false, true); ++It)
2964  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_cxx_isystem, It->Path, SA);
2965  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::ObjCSystem}, false, true); ++It)
2966  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_objc_isystem, It->Path, SA);
2967  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::ObjCXXSystem}, false, true); ++It)
2968  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_objcxx_isystem, It->Path, SA);
2969 
2970  // Add the internal paths from a driver that detects standard include paths.
2971  // Note: Some paths that came from "-internal-isystem" arguments may have
2972  // already been generated as "-isystem". If that's the case, their position on
2973  // command line was such that this has no semantic impact on include paths.
2974  for (; It < End &&
2975  Matches(*It, {frontend::System, frontend::ExternCSystem}, false, true);
2976  ++It) {
2977  OptSpecifier Opt = It->Group == frontend::System
2978  ? OPT_internal_isystem
2979  : OPT_internal_externc_isystem;
2980  GenerateArg(Args, Opt, It->Path, SA);
2981  }
2982 
2983  assert(It == End && "Unhandled HeaderSearchOption::Entry.");
2984 
2985  // Add the path prefixes which are implicitly treated as being system headers.
2986  for (const auto &P : Opts.SystemHeaderPrefixes) {
2987  OptSpecifier Opt = P.IsSystemHeader ? OPT_system_header_prefix
2988  : OPT_no_system_header_prefix;
2989  GenerateArg(Args, Opt, P.Prefix, SA);
2990  }
2991 
2992  for (const std::string &F : Opts.VFSOverlayFiles)
2993  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_ivfsoverlay, F, SA);
2994 }

2996 static bool ParseHeaderSearchArgs(HeaderSearchOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
2997  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
2998  const std::string &WorkingDir) {
2999  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
3000 
3001  HeaderSearchOptions *HeaderSearchOpts = &Opts;
3002 
3003 #define HEADER_SEARCH_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
3004  PREFIX_TYPE, NAME, ID, KIND, GROUP, ALIAS, ALIASARGS, FLAGS, PARAM, \
3005  HELPTEXT, METAVAR, VALUES, SPELLING, SHOULD_PARSE, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, \
3006  DEFAULT_VALUE, IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, DENORMALIZER, \
3007  MERGER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX) \
3008  PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
3009  Args, Diags, ID, FLAGS, PARAM, SHOULD_PARSE, KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE, \
3010  IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, MERGER, TABLE_INDEX)
3011 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
3012 #undef HEADER_SEARCH_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
3013 
3014  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_stdlib_EQ))
3015  Opts.UseLibcxx = (strcmp(A->getValue(), "libc++") == 0);
3016 
3017  // Canonicalize -fmodules-cache-path before storing it.
3018  SmallString<128> P(Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_fmodules_cache_path));
3019  if (!(P.empty() || llvm::sys::path::is_absolute(P))) {
3020  if (WorkingDir.empty())
3021  llvm::sys::fs::make_absolute(P);
3022  else
3023  llvm::sys::fs::make_absolute(WorkingDir, P);
3024  }
3025  llvm::sys::path::remove_dots(P);
3026  Opts.ModuleCachePath = std::string(P.str());
3027 
3028  // Only the -fmodule-file=<name>=<file> form.
3029  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fmodule_file)) {
3030  StringRef Val = A->getValue();
3031  if (Val.contains('=')) {
3032  auto Split = Val.split('=');
3033  Opts.PrebuiltModuleFiles.insert(
3034  {std::string(Split.first), std::string(Split.second)});
3035  }
3036  }
3037  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fprebuilt_module_path))
3038  Opts.AddPrebuiltModulePath(A->getValue());
3039 
3040  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fmodules_ignore_macro)) {
3041  StringRef MacroDef = A->getValue();
3042  Opts.ModulesIgnoreMacros.insert(
3043  llvm::CachedHashString(MacroDef.split('=').first));
3044  }
3045 
3046  // Add -I..., -F..., and -index-header-map options in order.
3047  bool IsIndexHeaderMap = false;
3048  bool IsSysrootSpecified =
3049  Args.hasArg(OPT__sysroot_EQ) || Args.hasArg(OPT_isysroot);
3050  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_I, OPT_F, OPT_index_header_map)) {
3051  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_index_header_map)) {
3052  // -index-header-map applies to the next -I or -F.
3053  IsIndexHeaderMap = true;
3054  continue;
3055  }
3056 
3057  frontend::IncludeDirGroup Group =
3058  IsIndexHeaderMap ? frontend::IndexHeaderMap : frontend::Angled;
3059 
3060  bool IsFramework = A->getOption().matches(OPT_F);
3061  std::string Path = A->getValue();
3062 
3063  if (IsSysrootSpecified && !IsFramework && A->getValue()[0] == '=') {
3064  SmallString<32> Buffer;
3065  llvm::sys::path::append(Buffer, Opts.Sysroot,
3066  llvm::StringRef(A->getValue()).substr(1));
3067  Path = std::string(Buffer.str());
3068  }
3069 
3070  Opts.AddPath(Path, Group, IsFramework,
3071  /*IgnoreSysroot*/ true);
3072  IsIndexHeaderMap = false;
3073  }
3074 
3075  // Add -iprefix/-iwithprefix/-iwithprefixbefore options.
3076  StringRef Prefix = ""; // FIXME: This isn't the correct default prefix.
3077  for (const auto *A :
3078  Args.filtered(OPT_iprefix, OPT_iwithprefix, OPT_iwithprefixbefore)) {
3079  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_iprefix))
3080  Prefix = A->getValue();
3081  else if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_iwithprefix))
3082  Opts.AddPath(Prefix.str() + A->getValue(), frontend::After, false, true);
3083  else
3084  Opts.AddPath(Prefix.str() + A->getValue(), frontend::Angled, false, true);
3085  }
3086 
3087  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_idirafter))
3088  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::After, false, true);
3089  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_iquote))
3090  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::Quoted, false, true);
3091  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_isystem, OPT_iwithsysroot))
3092  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::System, false,
3093  !A->getOption().matches(OPT_iwithsysroot));
3094  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_iframework))
3095  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::System, true, true);
3096  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_iframeworkwithsysroot))
3097  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::System, /*IsFramework=*/true,
3098  /*IgnoreSysRoot=*/false);
3099 
3100  // Add the paths for the various language specific isystem flags.
3101  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_c_isystem))
3102  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::CSystem, false, true);
3103  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_cxx_isystem))
3104  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::CXXSystem, false, true);
3105  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_objc_isystem))
3106  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::ObjCSystem, false,true);
3107  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_objcxx_isystem))
3108  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::ObjCXXSystem, false, true);
3109 
3110  // Add the internal paths from a driver that detects standard include paths.
3111  for (const auto *A :
3112  Args.filtered(OPT_internal_isystem, OPT_internal_externc_isystem)) {
3113  frontend::IncludeDirGroup Group = frontend::System;
3114  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_internal_externc_isystem))
3115  Group = frontend::ExternCSystem;
3116  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), Group, false, true);
3117  }
3118 
3119  // Add the path prefixes which are implicitly treated as being system headers.
3120  for (const auto *A :
3121  Args.filtered(OPT_system_header_prefix, OPT_no_system_header_prefix))
3122  Opts.AddSystemHeaderPrefix(
3123  A->getValue(), A->getOption().matches(OPT_system_header_prefix));
3124 
3125  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_ivfsoverlay))
3126  Opts.AddVFSOverlayFile(A->getValue());
3127 
3128  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
3129 }

3131 void CompilerInvocation::setLangDefaults(LangOptions &Opts, InputKind IK,
3132  const llvm::Triple &T,
3133  std::vector<std::string> &Includes,
3134  LangStandard::Kind LangStd) {
3135  // Set some properties which depend solely on the input kind; it would be nice
3136  // to move these to the language standard, and have the driver resolve the
3137  // input kind + language standard.
3138  //
3139  // FIXME: Perhaps a better model would be for a single source file to have
3140  // multiple language standards (C / C++ std, ObjC std, OpenCL std, OpenMP std)
3141  // simultaneously active?
3142  if (IK.getLanguage() == Language::Asm) {
3143  Opts.AsmPreprocessor = 1;
3144  } else if (IK.isObjectiveC()) {
3145  Opts.ObjC = 1;
3146  }
3147 
3148  if (LangStd == LangStandard::lang_unspecified) {
3149  // Based on the base language, pick one.
3150  switch (IK.getLanguage()) {
3151  case Language::Unknown:
3152  case Language::LLVM_IR:
3153  llvm_unreachable("Invalid input kind!");
3154  case Language::OpenCL:
3155  LangStd = LangStandard::lang_opencl12;
3156  break;
3157  case Language::OpenCLCXX:
3158  LangStd = LangStandard::lang_openclcpp10;
3159  break;
3160  case Language::CUDA:
3161  LangStd = LangStandard::lang_cuda;
3162  break;
3163  case Language::Asm:
3164  case Language::C:
3165 #if defined(CLANG_DEFAULT_STD_C)
3166  LangStd = CLANG_DEFAULT_STD_C;
3167 #else
3168  // The PS4 uses C99 as the default C standard.
3169  if (T.isPS4())
3170  LangStd = LangStandard::lang_gnu99;
3171  else
3172  LangStd = LangStandard::lang_gnu17;
3173 #endif
3174  break;
3175  case Language::ObjC:
3176 #if defined(CLANG_DEFAULT_STD_C)
3177  LangStd = CLANG_DEFAULT_STD_C;
3178 #else
3179  LangStd = LangStandard::lang_gnu11;
3180 #endif
3181  break;
3182  case Language::CXX:
3183  case Language::ObjCXX:
3184 #if defined(CLANG_DEFAULT_STD_CXX)
3185  LangStd = CLANG_DEFAULT_STD_CXX;
3186 #else
3187  LangStd = LangStandard::lang_gnucxx14;
3188 #endif
3189  break;
3190  case Language::RenderScript:
3191  LangStd = LangStandard::lang_c99;
3192  break;
3193  case Language::HIP:
3194  LangStd = LangStandard::lang_hip;
3195  break;
3196  }
3197  }
3198 
3199  const LangStandard &Std = LangStandard::getLangStandardForKind(LangStd);
3200  Opts.LangStd = LangStd;
3201  Opts.LineComment = Std.hasLineComments();
3202  Opts.C99 = Std.isC99();
3203  Opts.C11 = Std.isC11();
3204  Opts.C17 = Std.isC17();
3205  Opts.C2x = Std.isC2x();
3206  Opts.CPlusPlus = Std.isCPlusPlus();
3207  Opts.CPlusPlus11 = Std.isCPlusPlus11();
3208  Opts.CPlusPlus14 = Std.isCPlusPlus14();
3209  Opts.CPlusPlus17 = Std.isCPlusPlus17();
3210  Opts.CPlusPlus20 = Std.isCPlusPlus20();
3211  Opts.CPlusPlus2b = Std.isCPlusPlus2b();
3212  Opts.GNUMode = Std.isGNUMode();
3213  Opts.GNUCVersion = 0;
3214  Opts.HexFloats = Std.hasHexFloats();
3215  Opts.ImplicitInt = Std.hasImplicitInt();
3216 
3217  // Set OpenCL Version.
3218  Opts.OpenCL = Std.isOpenCL();
3219  if (LangStd == LangStandard::lang_opencl10)
3220  Opts.OpenCLVersion = 100;
3221  else if (LangStd == LangStandard::lang_opencl11)
3222  Opts.OpenCLVersion = 110;
3223  else if (LangStd == LangStandard::lang_opencl12)
3224  Opts.OpenCLVersion = 120;
3225  else if (LangStd == LangStandard::lang_opencl20)
3226  Opts.OpenCLVersion = 200;
3227  else if (LangStd == LangStandard::lang_opencl30)
3228  Opts.OpenCLVersion = 300;
3229  else if (LangStd == LangStandard::lang_openclcpp10)
3230  Opts.OpenCLCPlusPlusVersion = 100;
3231  else if (LangStd == LangStandard::lang_openclcpp2021)
3232  Opts.OpenCLCPlusPlusVersion = 202100;
3233 
3234  // OpenCL has some additional defaults.
3235  if (Opts.OpenCL) {
3236  Opts.AltiVec = 0;
3237  Opts.ZVector = 0;
3238  Opts.setDefaultFPContractMode(LangOptions::FPM_On);
3239  Opts.OpenCLCPlusPlus = Opts.CPlusPlus;
3240  Opts.OpenCLPipes = Opts.getOpenCLCompatibleVersion() == 200;
3241  Opts.OpenCLGenericAddressSpace = Opts.getOpenCLCompatibleVersion() == 200;
3242 
3243  // Include default header file for OpenCL.
3244  if (Opts.IncludeDefaultHeader) {
3245  if (Opts.DeclareOpenCLBuiltins) {
3246  // Only include base header file for builtin types and constants.
3247  Includes.push_back("opencl-c-base.h");
3248  } else {
3249  Includes.push_back("opencl-c.h");
3250  }
3251  }
3252  }
3253 
3254  Opts.HIP = IK.getLanguage() == Language::HIP;
3255  Opts.CUDA = IK.getLanguage() == Language::CUDA || Opts.HIP;
3256  if (Opts.HIP) {
3257  // HIP toolchain does not support 'Fast' FPOpFusion in backends since it
3258  // fuses multiplication/addition instructions without contract flag from
3259  // device library functions in LLVM bitcode, which causes accuracy loss in
3260  // certain math functions, e.g. tan(-1e20) becomes -0.933 instead of 0.8446.
3261  // For device library functions in bitcode to work, 'Strict' or 'Standard'
3262  // FPOpFusion options in backends is needed. Therefore 'fast-honor-pragmas'
3263  // FP contract option is used to allow fuse across statements in frontend
3264  // whereas respecting contract flag in backend.
3265  Opts.setDefaultFPContractMode(LangOptions::FPM_FastHonorPragmas);
3266  } else if (Opts.CUDA) {
3267  // Allow fuse across statements disregarding pragmas.
3268  Opts.setDefaultFPContractMode(LangOptions::FPM_Fast);
3269  }
3270 
3271  Opts.RenderScript = IK.getLanguage() == Language::RenderScript;
3272 
3273  // OpenCL, C++ and C2x have bool, true, false keywords.
3274  Opts.Bool = Opts.OpenCL || Opts.CPlusPlus || Opts.C2x;
3275 
3276  // OpenCL has half keyword
3277  Opts.Half = Opts.OpenCL;
3278 }

3280 /// Check if input file kind and language standard are compatible.
3281 static bool IsInputCompatibleWithStandard(InputKind IK,
3282  const LangStandard &S) {
3283  switch (IK.getLanguage()) {
3284  case Language::Unknown:
3285  case Language::LLVM_IR:
3286  llvm_unreachable("should not parse language flags for this input");
3287 
3288  case Language::C:
3289  case Language::ObjC:
3290  case Language::RenderScript:
3291  return S.getLanguage() == Language::C;
3292 
3293  case Language::OpenCL:
3294  return S.getLanguage() == Language::OpenCL ||
3295  S.getLanguage() == Language::OpenCLCXX;
3296 
3297  case Language::OpenCLCXX:
3298  return S.getLanguage() == Language::OpenCLCXX;
3299 
3300  case Language::CXX:
3301  case Language::ObjCXX:
3302  return S.getLanguage() == Language::CXX;
3303 
3304  case Language::CUDA:
3305  // FIXME: What -std= values should be permitted for CUDA compilations?
3306  return S.getLanguage() == Language::CUDA ||
3307  S.getLanguage() == Language::CXX;
3308 
3309  case Language::HIP:
3310  return S.getLanguage() == Language::CXX || S.getLanguage() == Language::HIP;
3311 
3312  case Language::Asm:
3313  // Accept (and ignore) all -std= values.
3314  // FIXME: The -std= value is not ignored; it affects the tokenization
3315  // and preprocessing rules if we're preprocessing this asm input.
3316  return true;
3317  }
3318 
3319  llvm_unreachable("unexpected input language");
3320 }

3643 bool CompilerInvocation::ParseLangArgs(LangOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
3644  InputKind IK, const llvm::Triple &T,
3645  std::vector<std::string> &Includes,
3646  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
3647  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
3648 
3649  if (IK.getFormat() == InputKind::Precompiled ||
3650  IK.getLanguage() == Language::LLVM_IR) {
3651  // ObjCAAutoRefCount and Sanitize LangOpts are used to setup the
3652  // PassManager in BackendUtil.cpp. They need to be initialized no matter
3653  // what the input type is.
3654  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fobjc_arc))
3655  Opts.ObjCAutoRefCount = 1;
3656  // PICLevel and PIELevel are needed during code generation and this should
3657  // be set regardless of the input type.
3658  Opts.PICLevel = getLastArgIntValue(Args, OPT_pic_level, 0, Diags);
3659  Opts.PIE = Args.hasArg(OPT_pic_is_pie);
3660  parseSanitizerKinds("-fsanitize=", Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_fsanitize_EQ),
3661  Diags, Opts.Sanitize);
3662 
3663  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
3664  }
3665 
3666  // Other LangOpts are only initialized when the input is not AST or LLVM IR.
3667  // FIXME: Should we really be parsing this for an Language::Asm input?
3668 
3669  // FIXME: Cleanup per-file based stuff.
3670  LangStandard::Kind LangStd = LangStandard::lang_unspecified;
3671  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_std_EQ)) {
3672  LangStd = LangStandard::getLangKind(A->getValue());
3673  if (LangStd == LangStandard::lang_unspecified) {
3674  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
3675  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
3676  // Report supported standards with short description.
3677  for (unsigned KindValue = 0;
3678  KindValue != LangStandard::lang_unspecified;
