4143  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver4);
4144  else if (Major <= 6)
4145  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver6);
4146  else if (Major <= 7)
4147  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver7);
4148  else if (Major <= 9)
4149  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver9);
4150  else if (Major <= 11)
4151  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver11);
4152  else if (Major <= 12)
4153  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver12);
4154  else if (Major <= 13)
4155  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver13);
4156  } else if (Ver != "latest") {
4157  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
4158  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
4159  }
4160  }
4161 
4162  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_msign_return_address_EQ)) {
4163  StringRef SignScope = A->getValue();
4164 
4165  if (SignScope.equals_insensitive("none"))
4166  Opts.setSignReturnAddressScope(
4167  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressScopeKind::None);
4168  else if (SignScope.equals_insensitive("all"))
4169  Opts.setSignReturnAddressScope(
4170  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressScopeKind::All);
4171  else if (SignScope.equals_insensitive("non-leaf"))
4172  Opts.setSignReturnAddressScope(
4173  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressScopeKind::NonLeaf);
4174  else
4175  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
4176  << A->getAsString(Args) << SignScope;
4177 
4178  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_msign_return_address_key_EQ)) {
4179  StringRef SignKey = A->getValue();
4180  if (!SignScope.empty() && !SignKey.empty()) {
4181  if (SignKey.equals_insensitive("a_key"))
4182  Opts.setSignReturnAddressKey(
4183  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressKeyKind::AKey);
4184  else if (SignKey.equals_insensitive("b_key"))
4185  Opts.setSignReturnAddressKey(
4186  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressKeyKind::BKey);
4187  else
4188  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
4189  << A->getAsString(Args) << SignKey;
4190  }
4191  }
4192  }
4193 
4194  // The value can be empty, which indicates the system default should be used.
4195  StringRef CXXABI = Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_fcxx_abi_EQ);
4196  if (!CXXABI.empty()) {
4197  if (!TargetCXXABI::isABI(CXXABI)) {
4198  Diags.Report(diag::err_invalid_cxx_abi) << CXXABI;
4199  } else {
4200  auto Kind = TargetCXXABI::getKind(CXXABI);
4201  if (!TargetCXXABI::isSupportedCXXABI(T, Kind))
4202  Diags.Report(diag::err_unsupported_cxx_abi) << CXXABI << T.str();
4203  else
4204  Opts.CXXABI = Kind;
4205  }
4206  }
4207 
4208  Opts.RelativeCXXABIVTables =
4209  Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fexperimental_relative_cxx_abi_vtables,
4210  options::OPT_fno_experimental_relative_cxx_abi_vtables,
4211  TargetCXXABI::usesRelativeVTables(T));
4212 
4213  for (const auto &A : Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_fmacro_prefix_map_EQ)) {
4214  auto Split = StringRef(A).split('=');
4215  Opts.MacroPrefixMap.insert(
4216  {std::string(Split.first), std::string(Split.second)});
4217  }
4218 
4219  // Error if -mvscale-min is unbounded.
4220  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mvscale_min_EQ)) {
4221  unsigned VScaleMin;
4222  if (StringRef(A->getValue()).getAsInteger(10, VScaleMin) || VScaleMin == 0)
4223  Diags.Report(diag::err_cc1_unbounded_vscale_min);
4224  }
4225 
4226  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
4227 }

4234  case frontend::ASTView:

4236  case frontend::EmitBC:
4237  case frontend::EmitHTML:

4275 static void GeneratePreprocessorArgs(PreprocessorOptions &Opts,
4276  SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
4277  CompilerInvocation::StringAllocator SA,
4278  const LangOptions &LangOpts,
4279  const FrontendOptions &FrontendOpts,
4280  const CodeGenOptions &CodeGenOpts) {
4281  PreprocessorOptions *PreprocessorOpts = &Opts;
4282 
4283 #define PREPROCESSOR_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
4284  PREFIX_TYPE, NAME, ID, KIND, GROUP, ALIAS, ALIASARGS, FLAGS, PARAM, \
4285  HELPTEXT, METAVAR, VALUES, SPELLING, SHOULD_PARSE, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, \
4286  DEFAULT_VALUE, IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, DENORMALIZER, \
4287  MERGER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX) \
4288  GENERATE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
4289  Args, SA, KIND, FLAGS, SPELLING, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE, \
4290  IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, DENORMALIZER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX)
4291 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
4292 #undef PREPROCESSOR_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
4293 
4294  if (Opts.PCHWithHdrStop && !Opts.PCHWithHdrStopCreate)
4295  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_pch_through_hdrstop_use, SA);
4296 
4297  for (const auto &D : Opts.DeserializedPCHDeclsToErrorOn)
4298  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_error_on_deserialized_pch_decl, D, SA);
4299 
4300  if (Opts.PrecompiledPreambleBytes != std::make_pair(0u, false))
4301  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_preamble_bytes_EQ,
4302  Twine(Opts.PrecompiledPreambleBytes.first) + "," +
4303  (Opts.PrecompiledPreambleBytes.second ? "1" : "0"),
4304  SA);
4305 
4306  for (const auto &M : Opts.Macros) {
4307  // Don't generate __CET__ macro definitions. They are implied by the
4308  // -fcf-protection option that is generated elsewhere.
4309  if (M.first == "__CET__=1" && !M.second &&
4310  !CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionReturn && CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionBranch)
4311  continue;
4312  if (M.first == "__CET__=2" && !M.second && CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionReturn &&
4313  !CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionBranch)
4314  continue;
4315  if (M.first == "__CET__=3" && !M.second && CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionReturn &&
4316  CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionBranch)
4317  continue;
4318 
4319  GenerateArg(Args, M.second ? OPT_U : OPT_D, M.first, SA);
4320  }
4321 
4322  for (const auto &I : Opts.Includes) {
4323  // Don't generate OpenCL includes. They are implied by other flags that are
4324  // generated elsewhere.
4325  if (LangOpts.OpenCL && LangOpts.IncludeDefaultHeader &&
4326  ((LangOpts.DeclareOpenCLBuiltins && I == "opencl-c-base.h") ||
4327  I == "opencl-c.h"))
4328  continue;
4329 
4330  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_include, I, SA);
4331  }
4332 
4333  for (const auto &CI : Opts.ChainedIncludes)
4334  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_chain_include, CI, SA);
4335 
4336  for (const auto &RF : Opts.RemappedFiles)
4337  GenerateArg(Args, OPT_remap_file, RF.first + ";" + RF.second, SA);
4338 
4339  // Don't handle LexEditorPlaceholders. It is implied by the action that is
4340  // generated elsewhere.
4341 }

4343 static bool ParsePreprocessorArgs(PreprocessorOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
4344  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
4345  frontend::ActionKind Action,
4346  const FrontendOptions &FrontendOpts) {
4347  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
4348 
4349  PreprocessorOptions *PreprocessorOpts = &Opts;
4350 
4351 #define PREPROCESSOR_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
4352  PREFIX_TYPE, NAME, ID, KIND, GROUP, ALIAS, ALIASARGS, FLAGS, PARAM, \
4353  HELPTEXT, METAVAR, VALUES, SPELLING, SHOULD_PARSE, ALWAYS_EMIT, KEYPATH, \
4354  DEFAULT_VALUE, IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, DENORMALIZER, \
4355  MERGER, EXTRACTOR, TABLE_INDEX) \
4356  PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING( \
4357  Args, Diags, ID, FLAGS, PARAM, SHOULD_PARSE, KEYPATH, DEFAULT_VALUE, \
4358  IMPLIED_CHECK, IMPLIED_VALUE, NORMALIZER, MERGER, TABLE_INDEX)
4359 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
4360 #undef PREPROCESSOR_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
4361 
4362  Opts.PCHWithHdrStop = Args.hasArg(OPT_pch_through_hdrstop_create) ||
4363  Args.hasArg(OPT_pch_through_hdrstop_use);
4364 
4365  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_error_on_deserialized_pch_decl))
4366  Opts.DeserializedPCHDeclsToErrorOn.insert(A->getValue());
4367 
4368  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_preamble_bytes_EQ)) {
4369  StringRef Value(A->getValue());
4370  size_t Comma = Value.find(',');
4371  unsigned Bytes = 0;
4372  unsigned EndOfLine = 0;
4373 
4374  if (Comma == StringRef::npos ||
4375  Value.substr(0, Comma).getAsInteger(10, Bytes) ||
4376  Value.substr(Comma + 1).getAsInteger(10, EndOfLine))
4377  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_preamble_format);
4378  else {
4379  Opts.PrecompiledPreambleBytes.first = Bytes;
4380  Opts.PrecompiledPreambleBytes.second = (EndOfLine != 0);
4381  }
4382  }
4383 
4384  // Add the __CET__ macro if a CFProtection option is set.
4385  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_fcf_protection_EQ)) {
4386  StringRef Name = A->getValue();
4387  if (Name == "branch")
4388  Opts.addMacroDef("__CET__=1");
4389  else if (Name == "return")
4390  Opts.addMacroDef("__CET__=2");
4391  else if (Name == "full")
4392  Opts.addMacroDef("__CET__=3");
4393  }
4394 
4395  // Add macros from the command line.
4396  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_D, OPT_U)) {
4397  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_D))
4398  Opts.addMacroDef(A->getValue());
4399  else
4400  Opts.addMacroUndef(A->getValue());
4401  }
4402 
4403  // Add the ordered list of -includes.
4404  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_include))
4405  Opts.Includes.emplace_back(A->getValue());
4406 
4407  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_chain_include))
4408  Opts.ChainedIncludes.emplace_back(A->getValue());
4409 
4410  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_remap_file)) {
4411  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split = StringRef(A->getValue()).split(';');
4412 
4413  if (Split.second.empty()) {
4414  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_remap_file) << A->getAsString(Args);
4415  continue;
4416  }
4417 
4418  Opts.addRemappedFile(Split.first, Split.second);
4419  }
4420 
4421  // Always avoid lexing editor placeholders when we're just running the
4422  // preprocessor as we never want to emit the
4423  // "editor placeholder in source file" error in PP only mode.
4424  if (isStrictlyPreprocessorAction(Action))
4425  Opts.LexEditorPlaceholders = false;
4426 
4427  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
4428 }

4554 bool CompilerInvocation::CreateFromArgsImpl(
4555  CompilerInvocation &Res, ArrayRef<const char *> CommandLineArgs,
4556  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags, const char *Argv0) {
4557  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
4558 
4559  // Parse the arguments.
4560  const OptTable &Opts = getDriverOptTable();
4561  const unsigned IncludedFlagsBitmask = options::CC1Option;
4562  unsigned MissingArgIndex, MissingArgCount;
4563  InputArgList Args = Opts.ParseArgs(CommandLineArgs, MissingArgIndex,
4564  MissingArgCount, IncludedFlagsBitmask);
4565  LangOptions &LangOpts = *Res.getLangOpts();
4566 
4567  // Check for missing argument error.
4568  if (MissingArgCount)
4569  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_missing_argument)
4570  << Args.getArgString(MissingArgIndex) << MissingArgCount;
4571 
4572  // Issue errors on unknown arguments.
4573  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_UNKNOWN)) {
4574  auto ArgString = A->getAsString(Args);
4575  std::string Nearest;
4576  if (Opts.findNearest(ArgString, Nearest, IncludedFlagsBitmask) > 1)
4577  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_unknown_argument) << ArgString;
4578  else
4579  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_unknown_argument_with_suggestion)
4580  << ArgString << Nearest;
4581  }
4582 
4583  ParseFileSystemArgs(Res.getFileSystemOpts(), Args, Diags);
4584  ParseMigratorArgs(Res.getMigratorOpts(), Args, Diags);
4585  ParseAnalyzerArgs(*Res.getAnalyzerOpts(), Args, Diags);
4586  ParseDiagnosticArgs(Res.getDiagnosticOpts(), Args, &Diags,
4587  /*DefaultDiagColor=*/false);
4588  ParseFrontendArgs(Res.getFrontendOpts(), Args, Diags, LangOpts.IsHeaderFile);
4589  // FIXME: We shouldn't have to pass the DashX option around here
4590  InputKind DashX = Res.getFrontendOpts().DashX;
4591  ParseTargetArgs(Res.getTargetOpts(), Args, Diags);
4592  llvm::Triple T(Res.getTargetOpts().Triple);
4593  ParseHeaderSearchArgs(Res.getHeaderSearchOpts(), Args, Diags,
4594  Res.getFileSystemOpts().WorkingDir);
4595 
4596  ParseLangArgs(LangOpts, Args, DashX, T, Res.getPreprocessorOpts().Includes,
4597  Diags);
4598  if (Res.getFrontendOpts().ProgramAction == frontend::RewriteObjC)
4599  LangOpts.ObjCExceptions = 1;
4600 
4601  if (LangOpts.CUDA) {
4602  // During CUDA device-side compilation, the aux triple is the
4603  // triple used for host compilation.
4604  if (LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice)
4605  Res.getTargetOpts().HostTriple = Res.getFrontendOpts().AuxTriple;
4606  }
4607 
4608  // Set the triple of the host for OpenMP device compile.
4609  if (LangOpts.OpenMPIsDevice)
4610  Res.getTargetOpts().HostTriple = Res.getFrontendOpts().AuxTriple;
4611 
4612  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
4613  // Set the triple of the host for SYCL device compile.
4614  Res.getTargetOpts().HostTriple = Res.getFrontendOpts().AuxTriple;
4615  // If specified, create empty integration header files for now.
4616  CreateEmptyFile(LangOpts.SYCLIntHeader);
4617  CreateEmptyFile(LangOpts.SYCLIntFooter);
4618  }
4619 
4620  ParseCodeGenArgs(Res.getCodeGenOpts(), Args, DashX, Diags, T,
4621  Res.getFrontendOpts().OutputFile, LangOpts);
4622 
4623  // FIXME: Override value name discarding when asan or msan is used because the
4624  // backend passes depend on the name of the alloca in order to print out
4625  // names.
4626  Res.getCodeGenOpts().DiscardValueNames &=
4627  !LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Address) &&
4628  !LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::KernelAddress) &&
4629  !LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Memory) &&
4630  !LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::KernelMemory);
4631 
4632  ParsePreprocessorArgs(Res.getPreprocessorOpts(), Args, Diags,
4633  Res.getFrontendOpts().ProgramAction,
4634  Res.getFrontendOpts());
4635  ParsePreprocessorOutputArgs(Res.getPreprocessorOutputOpts(), Args, Diags,
4636  Res.getFrontendOpts().ProgramAction);
4637 
4638  ParseDependencyOutputArgs(Res.getDependencyOutputOpts(), Args, Diags,
4639  Res.getFrontendOpts().ProgramAction,
4640  Res.getPreprocessorOutputOpts().ShowLineMarkers);
4641  if (!Res.getDependencyOutputOpts().OutputFile.empty() &&
4642  Res.getDependencyOutputOpts().Targets.empty())
4643  Diags.Report(diag::err_fe_dependency_file_requires_MT);
4644 
4645  // If sanitizer is enabled, disable OPT_ffine_grained_bitfield_accesses.
4646  if (Res.getCodeGenOpts().FineGrainedBitfieldAccesses &&
4647  !Res.getLangOpts()->Sanitize.empty()) {
4648  Res.getCodeGenOpts().FineGrainedBitfieldAccesses = false;
4649  Diags.Report(diag::warn_drv_fine_grained_bitfield_accesses_ignored);
4650  }
4651 
4652  // Store the command-line for using in the CodeView backend.
4653  Res.getCodeGenOpts().Argv0 = Argv0;
4654  append_range(Res.getCodeGenOpts().CommandLineArgs, CommandLineArgs);
4655 
4656  FixupInvocation(Res, Diags, Args, DashX);
4657 
4658  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
4659 }

4677 std::string CompilerInvocation::getModuleHash() const {
4678  // FIXME: Consider using SHA1 instead of MD5.
4679  llvm::HashBuilder<llvm::MD5, llvm::support::endianness::native> HBuilder;
4680 
4681  // Note: For QoI reasons, the things we use as a hash here should all be
4682  // dumped via the -module-info flag.
4683 
4684  // Start the signature with the compiler version.
4685  HBuilder.add(getClangFullRepositoryVersion());
4686 
4687  // Also include the serialization version, in case LLVM_APPEND_VC_REV is off
4688  // and getClangFullRepositoryVersion() doesn't include git revision.
4689  HBuilder.add(serialization::VERSION_MAJOR, serialization::VERSION_MINOR);
4690 
4691  // Extend the signature with the language options
4692 #define LANGOPT(Name, Bits, Default, Description) HBuilder.add(LangOpts->Name);
4693 #define ENUM_LANGOPT(Name, Type, Bits, Default, Description) \
4694  HBuilder.add(static_cast<unsigned>(LangOpts->get##Name()));
4695 #define BENIGN_LANGOPT(Name, Bits, Default, Description)
4696 #define BENIGN_ENUM_LANGOPT(Name, Type, Bits, Default, Description)
4697 #include "clang/Basic/LangOptions.def"
4698 
4699  HBuilder.addRange(LangOpts->ModuleFeatures);
4700 
4701  HBuilder.add(LangOpts->ObjCRuntime);
4702  HBuilder.addRange(LangOpts->CommentOpts.BlockCommandNames);
4703 
4704  // Extend the signature with the target options.
4705  HBuilder.add(TargetOpts->Triple, TargetOpts->CPU, TargetOpts->TuneCPU,
4706  TargetOpts->ABI);
4707  HBuilder.addRange(TargetOpts->FeaturesAsWritten);
4708 
4709  // Extend the signature with preprocessor options.
4710  const PreprocessorOptions &ppOpts = getPreprocessorOpts();
4711  HBuilder.add(ppOpts.UsePredefines, ppOpts.DetailedRecord);
4712 
4713  const HeaderSearchOptions &hsOpts = getHeaderSearchOpts();
4714  for (const auto &Macro : getPreprocessorOpts().Macros) {
4715  // If we're supposed to ignore this macro for the purposes of modules,
4716  // don't put it into the hash.
4717  if (!hsOpts.ModulesIgnoreMacros.empty()) {
4718  // Check whether we're ignoring this macro.
4719  StringRef MacroDef = Macro.first;
4720  if (hsOpts.ModulesIgnoreMacros.count(
4721  llvm::CachedHashString(MacroDef.split('=').first)))
4722  continue;
4723  }
4724 
4725  HBuilder.add(Macro);
4726  }
4727 
4728  // Extend the signature with the sysroot and other header search options.
4729  HBuilder.add(hsOpts.Sysroot, hsOpts.ModuleFormat, hsOpts.UseDebugInfo,
4730  hsOpts.UseBuiltinIncludes, hsOpts.UseStandardSystemIncludes,
4731  hsOpts.UseStandardCXXIncludes, hsOpts.UseLibcxx,
4732  hsOpts.ModulesValidateDiagnosticOptions);
4733  HBuilder.add(hsOpts.ResourceDir);
4734 
4735  if (hsOpts.ModulesStrictContextHash) {
4736  HBuilder.addRange(hsOpts.SystemHeaderPrefixes);
4737  HBuilder.addRange(hsOpts.UserEntries);
4738 
4739  const DiagnosticOptions &diagOpts = getDiagnosticOpts();
4740 #define DIAGOPT(Name, Bits, Default) HBuilder.add(diagOpts.Name);
4741 #define ENUM_DIAGOPT(Name, Type, Bits, Default) \
4742  HBuilder.add(diagOpts.get##Name());
4743 #include "clang/Basic/DiagnosticOptions.def"
4744 #undef DIAGOPT
4745 #undef ENUM_DIAGOPT
4746  }
4747 
4748  // Extend the signature with the user build path.
4749  HBuilder.add(hsOpts.ModuleUserBuildPath);
4750 
4751  // Extend the signature with the module file extensions.
4752  for (const auto &ext : getFrontendOpts().ModuleFileExtensions)
4753  ext->hashExtension(HBuilder);
4754 
4755  // When compiling with -gmodules, also hash -fdebug-prefix-map as it
4756  // affects the debug info in the PCM.
4757  if (getCodeGenOpts().DebugTypeExtRefs)
4758  HBuilder.addRange(getCodeGenOpts().DebugPrefixMap);
4759 
4760  // Extend the signature with the enabled sanitizers, if at least one is
4761  // enabled. Sanitizers which cannot affect AST generation aren't hashed.
4762  SanitizerSet SanHash = LangOpts->Sanitize;
4763  SanHash.clear(getPPTransparentSanitizers());
4764  if (!SanHash.empty())
4765  HBuilder.add(SanHash.Mask);
4766 
4767  llvm::MD5::MD5Result Result;
4768  HBuilder.getHasher().final(Result);
4769  uint64_t Hash = Result.high() ^ Result.low();
4770  return toString(llvm::APInt(64, Hash), 36, /*Signed=*/false);
4771 }

4801 IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem>
4802 clang::createVFSFromCompilerInvocation(
4803  const CompilerInvocation &CI, DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
4804  IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem> BaseFS) {
4805  if (CI.getHeaderSearchOpts().VFSOverlayFiles.empty())
4806  return BaseFS;
4807 
4808  IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem> Result = BaseFS;
4809  // earlier vfs files are on the bottom
4810  for (const auto &File : CI.getHeaderSearchOpts().VFSOverlayFiles) {
4811  llvm::ErrorOr<std::unique_ptr<llvm::MemoryBuffer>> Buffer =
4812  Result->getBufferForFile(File);
4813  if (!Buffer) {
4814  Diags.Report(diag::err_missing_vfs_overlay_file) << File;
4815  continue;
4816  }
4817 
4818  IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem> FS = llvm::vfs::getVFSFromYAML(
4819  std::move(Buffer.get()), /*DiagHandler*/ nullptr, File,
4820  /*DiagContext*/ nullptr, Result);
4821  if (!FS) {
4822  Diags.Report(diag::err_invalid_vfs_overlay) << File;
4823  continue;
4824  }
4825 
4826  Result = FS;
4827  }
4828  return Result;
4829 }
